INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (470001, 'One of the great attractions of patriotism - it fulfills our worst wishes. In the person of our nation we are able, vicariously, to bully and cheat. Bully and cheat, what''s more, with a feeling that we are profoundly virtuous.', 1032, 0), (470002, 'Better a little which is well done, than a great deal imperfectly.', 51, 0), (470003, 'Bananas are great, as I believe them to be the only known cure for existential dread. Also, Mother Teresa said that in India, a woman dying in the street will share her banana with anyone who needs it, whereas in America, people amass and hoard as many bananas as they can to sell for an exorbitant profit. So half of them go bad, anyway.', 457, 0), (470004, 'Take time for all things: great haste makes great waste.', 1077, 0), (470005, 'A great empire, like a great cake, is most easily diminished at the edges.', 1077, 0), (470006, 'Boredom always precedes a period of great creativity.', 1742, 0), (470007, 'It is of great use to the sailor to know the length of his line, though he cannot with it fathom all the depths of the ocean.', 2375, 0), (470008, 'Shave off your beard and wear a dress. You would be a great female impersonator.', 55901, 0), (470009, 'The very greatest things - great thoughts, discoveries, inventions - have usually been nurtured in hardship, often pondered over in sorrow, and at length established with difficulty.', 7329, 0), (470010, 'Atheism is aristocratic the idea of a great Being that watches over oppressed innocence and punishes triumphant crime is altogether popular. ', 71474, 0), (470011, 'Rugby is great. The players don''t wear helmets or padding they just beat the living daylights out of each other and then go for a beer. I love that. ', 12992, 0), (470012, 'You know, when you really connect with the instrument and everything just comes out on an emotional level very naturally through your playing. That''s, you know, a great night. And I think the reason I love touring so much is you''re chasing that high around all the time, trying to have another good night.', 22833, 0), (470013, 'Life is hard. Not great. Kind of tragic.', 67691, 0), (470014, 'Life in abundance comes only through great love.', 4, 0), (470015, 'Don''t be humble... you''re not that great.', 12971, 0), (470016, 'It is only the great hearted who can be true friends. The mean and cowardly, Can never know what true friendship means.', 3036, 0), (470017, 'The bravest sight in the world is to see a great man struggling against adversity.', 65434, 0), (470018, 'Hard times always lead to something great.', 55837, 0), (470019, 'If Heaven exists, to know that there''s laughter, that would be a great thing.', 2185, 0), (470020, 'Never give in - never, never, never, never, in nothing great or small, large or petty, never give in except to convictions of honour and good sense.', 3621, 0), (470021, 'Great moments are born from great oppurtunities.', 68183, 0), (470022, 'The sensitivity of men to small matters, and their indifference to great ones, indicates a strange inversion.', 144, 0), (470023, 'In terms of fashion, I love adding a fun scarf to whatever I''m wearing - it''s a great way to dress up a plain outfit!', 74182, 0), (470024, 'If you don''t think every day is a great day try going without one.', 69539, 0), (470025, 'The great tradition of Delhi can be seen through its cuisine.', 67868, 0), (470026, 'Great leaders are willing to sacrifice the numbers to save the people. Poor leaders sacrifice the people to save the numbers.', 19485, 0), (470027, 'Canada is like a loft apartment over a really great party.', 2185, 0), (470028, 'As we learned after President Herbert Hoover signed the Smoot-Hawley tariff at the outset of the Great Depression, vibrant international trade is a key component to economic recovery; hindering trade is a recipe for disaster.', 71383, 0), (470029, 'There never was any heart truly great and generous, that was not also tender and compassionate.', 35, 0), (470030, 'A great civilization is not conquered from without until it has destroyed itself from within.', 74183, 0), (470031, 'Working hard is great, being lazy sometimes is great, but failed potential is the worst.', 68499, 0), (470032, 'Dance is a great way to express yourself.', 68905, 0), (470033, 'An understanding of the natural world and what''s in it is a source of not only a great curiosity but great fulfillment.', 3969, 0), (470034, 'The first and greatest victory is to conquer yourself to be conquered by yourself is of all things most shameful and vile. ', 51, 0), (470035, 'For a selfie, it''s not about the pose, it''s about you. There''s a reason why you look great in the picture or you look great in real life, because someone has caught the essence of who you are, and a pose is not you.', 74184, 0), (470036, 'More enduringly than any other sport, wrestling teaches self-control and pride. Some have wrestled without great skill - none have wrestled without pride.', 59452, 0), (470037, 'When you sing with a group of people, you learn how to subsume yourself into a group consciousness because a capella singing is all about the immersion of the self into the community. That''s one of the great feelings - to stop being me for a little while and to become us. That way lies empathy, the great social virtue.', 18504, 0), (470038, 'Sheep farming is heavily subsidized in Great Britain. Without the subsidies, the green grazing in the valley of the River Exe would be gone. The handsome agricultural landscape of which the British are so proud, carefully husbanded since Boudicca''s day, would be replaced by natural growth. The most likely growth is real-estate developments.', 10731, 0), (470039, 'I am such a sap when it comes to love! I believe in love at first sight all the way. But that''s just the way it happened to me with my relationships. I love the idea of two people looking at each other and electricity flying around them; it''s so romantic, and it''s a great feeling.', 68103, 0), (470040, 'I want to keep meeting new people, enlarging my circle of friends. I have great friends now... really good people. But I''m always ready for what comes next.', 3232, 0), (470041, 'There is no way to be truly great in this world. We are all impaled on the crook of conditioning.', 1784, 0), (470042, 'We must always remember that America is a great nation today not because of what government did for people but because of what people did for themselves and for one another.', 9695, 0), (470043, 'Suffering becomes beautiful when anyone bears great calamities with cheerfulness, not through insensibility but through greatness of mind.', 1116, 0), (470044, 'I just follow great people. If you want to play like a pro, you learn from the pros.', 74185, 0), (470045, 'Do you have hands? Excellent. That''s a good start. Can you hold a pencil? Great. If you have a sketchbook, open it and start by making a line, a mark, wherever. Doodle.', 69876, 0), (470046, 'The great pleasure of a dog is that you may make a fool of yourself with him and not only will he not scold you, but he will make a fool of himself too.', 4111, 0), (470047, 'Rhetoric is a poor substitute for action, and we have trusted only to rhetoric. If we are really to be a great nation, we must not merely talk; we must act big.', 1674, 0), (470048, 'Great talents are the most lovely and often the most dangerous fruits on the tree of humanity. They hang upon the most slender twigs that are easily snapped off.', 28934, 0), (470049, 'Every day is a great day for hockey.', 72699, 0), (470050, 'Key West is the place where your sickly house plant back in New York grows to 10 ft. It''s also the place where an 8-ft. cactus, the century plant, produces a huge yellow flower every great once in a while, like a robot proffering a bouquet. After the plant flowers, it dies.', 9683, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (470051, 'Mental health needs a great deal of attention. It''s the final taboo and it needs to be faced and dealt with.', 31483, 0), (470052, 'One thing I always say is being a great chef today is not enough - you have to be a great businessman.', 72061, 0), (470053, 'I''ve also seen that great men are often lonely. This is understandable, because they have built such high standards for themselves that they often feel alone. But that same loneliness is part of their ability to create.', 58257, 0), (470054, 'There must be a beginning of any great matter, but the continuing unto the end until it be thoroughly finished yields the true glory.', 74186, 0), (470055, 'It''s always better to shock people and change people''s expectations than to give them exactly what they think you can do. It''s not unexpected for me to be in a comedy film anymore; I''m no longer the underdog in that world. Not that I''m great or good at it or anything, it''s just that I''ve done a bunch of them, so you''re not shocked.', 68889, 0), (470056, 'You will become as small as your controlling desire as great as you dominant aspiration. ', 2970, 0), (470057, 'I don''t think actors should ever expect to get a role, because the disappointment is too great. You''ve got to think of things as an opportunity. An audition''s an opportunity to have an audience.', 761, 0), (470058, 'A great hallmark of mental wellness is the ability to be in the present moment, fully and with no thoughts of being elsewhere.', 21729, 0), (470059, 'I''m living on this positive mind frame where I''m only attracting positive things. I''m controlling my energy, I''m eating right, I''m meditating, I''m in the gym, I''m doing all this stuff I''m supposed to be doing. I''m past that young, immature way of thinking. I just want to be great.', 71076, 0), (470060, 'No man is worth his salt who is not ready at all times to risk his well-being, to risk his body, to risk his life, in a great cause.', 1674, 0), (470061, 'Every great person is always being helped by everybody for their gift is to get good out of all things and all persons. ', 485, 0), (470062, 'A cloudy day or a little sunshine have as great an influence on many constitutions as the most recent blessings or misfortunes.', 2868, 0), (470063, 'Behind every great fortune lies a great crime.', 143, 0), (470064, 'To be really great in little things, to be truly noble and heroic in the insipid details of everyday life, is a virtue so rare as to be worthy of canonization.', 3252, 0), (470065, 'Small opportunities are often the beginning of great enterprises.', 3291, 0), (470066, 'I wanted to learn everything I could about what it takes to be a great chef. It was a turning point for me.', 1164, 0), (470067, 'It''s great to be a blonde. With low expectations it''s very easy to surprise people.', 26624, 0), (470068, 'Most men who have really lived have had, in some share, their great adventure. This railway is mine.', 73084, 0), (470069, 'With people of limited ability modesty is merely honesty. But with those who possess great talent it is hypocrisy.', 1304, 0), (470070, 'Not only are pasta dishes delicious, but they are also great, easy options for a quick dinner during a busy weekday.', 32425, 0), (470071, 'Great teaching requires incredible talent and dedication, strong intellectual ability and interpersonal skill, real discipline and empathy.', 71037, 0), (470072, 'There is a kind of elevation which does not depend on fortune; it is a certain air which distinguishes us, and seems to destine us for great things; it is a price which we imperceptibly set upon ourselves.', 154, 0), (470073, 'One of the greatest resources people cannot mobilize themselves is that they try to accomplish great things. Most worthwhile achievements are the result of many little things done in a single direction.', 37913, 0), (470074, 'A retentive memory may be a good thing, but the ability to forget is the true token of greatness.', 4, 0), (470075, 'If you want to be remembered as great, if you want to be a legend, you have to go out there every single day and do stuff.', 69347, 0), (470076, 'I think what motivates people is not great hate, but great love for other people.', 11495, 0), (470077, 'Tradition is the great misleader because it''s too easy to follow what has already been done - even though you may think you''re giving it a kick. I was really trying to invent, instead of merely expressing myself.', 1473, 0), (470078, 'After people have repeated a phrase a great number of times, they begin to realize it has meaning and may even be true.', 3173, 0), (470079, 'The first test of a truly great man is his humility. By humility I don''t mean doubt of his powers or hesitation in speaking his opinion, but merely an understanding of the relationship of what he can say and what he can do.', 485, 0), (470080, 'Action is greater than writing. A good man is a nobler object of contemplation than a great author. There are but two things worth living for: to do what is worthy of being written and to write what is worthy of being read. ', 66580, 0), (470081, 'Abuse of words has been the great instrument of sophistry and chicanery, of party, faction, and division of society.', 4179, 0), (470082, 'Where the willingness is great, the difficulties cannot be great.', 947, 0), (470083, 'Success has always been a great liar.', 11, 0), (470084, 'Blogging is a great way to show your talents and interests to prospective employers, while adding an edge to your resume. If you blog consistently it shows your dedication, passions and creativity - all of which are key attributes employers look for in job candidates.', 153, 0), (470085, 'The great thing about irony is that it splits things apart, gets up above them so we can see the flaws and hypocrisies and duplicates.', 209, 0), (470086, 'You learn their honesty, you learn their competitiveness. You learn a lot about a person. It''s not that they have to sink the putt and there''s a great deal of talent involved - but you do learn about how competitive a person is on the golf course, and frankly, how honest.', 64643, 0), (470087, 'Volunteering is a great way to look outside your own problems. Giving back to makes you happier by both giving you a sense of purpose and helping to put your problems in perspective.', 5238, 0), (470088, 'Great people talk about ideas, average people talk about things, and small people talk about wine.', 1437, 0), (470089, 'One would like to be grand and heroic, if one could; but if not, why try at all? One wants to be very something, very great, very heroic; or if not that, then at least very stylish and very fashionable. It is this everlasting mediocrity that bores me.', 3252, 0), (470090, 'The greatest good you can do for another is not just to share your riches but to reveal to him his own.', 1827, 0), (470091, 'Could a greater miracle take place than for us to look through each other''s eyes for an instant?', 1049, 0), (470092, 'I have learned to use the word ''impossible'' with the greatest caution.', 5463, 0), (470093, 'Great leaders communicate a vision that captures the imagination and fires the hearts and minds of those around them.', 4294, 0), (470094, 'Great lives never go out they go on. ', 45276, 0), (470095, 'It''s always great to get to do what you love and to do something that hopefully people will see and love.', 72056, 0), (470096, 'An ignorance of means may minister to greatness, but an ignorance of aims make it impossible to be great at all.', 157, 0), (470097, 'I never weary of great churches. It is my favorite kind of mountain scenery. Mankind was never so happily inspired as when it made a cathedral.', 449, 0), (470098, 'A successful entrepreneur can''t be afraid of failures or setbacks. An initial setback can be a great opportunity to take a new and more promising approach to any problem, to come back stronger than ever.', 74187, 0), (470099, 'My favorite foods are things that aren''t great to eat, like pizza.', 71112, 0), (470100, 'We''ve had great successes, but our future is not about our past success. It''s going to be about whether we will invent things that are really going to drive our future.', 54622, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (470101, 'All great empires die from within.', 67040, 0), (470102, 'The paradox is really the pathos of intellectual life and just as only great souls are exposed to passions it is only the great thinker who is exposed to what I call paradoxes, which are nothing else than grandiose thoughts in embryo.', 3131, 0), (470103, 'The difficulty is not so great to die for a friend, as to find a friend worth dying for.', 395, 0), (470104, 'Without an open-minded mind, you can never be a great success.', 37848, 0), (470105, 'Great ideology creates great times.', 72263, 0), (470106, 'In life, so many things are taken for granted, but one thing I can honestly say is that I took every day, enjoyed the game of putting on that uniform and playing the great game of baseball.', 5512, 0), (470107, 'Skateboarding helps a ton with balance, precision, with air awareness... it gets your senses to be spot-on and it''s also a great way to take my mind off things.', 67034, 0), (470108, 'Some people have a mistaken idea that all thoughts disappear through meditation and we enter a state of blankness. There certainly are times of great tranquility when concentration is strong and we have few, if any, thoughts. But other times, we can be flooded with memories, plans or random thinking. It''s important not to blame yourself.', 124, 0), (470109, 'Germany is a great nation only because its people have so much Polish blood in their veins.', 11, 0), (470110, 'We say arts education is good for general education, but that''s not the point. The arts are what great nations are remembered for. They are a mirror.', 74188, 0), (470111, 'All difficult things have their origin in that which is easy, and great things in that which is small.', 15, 0), (470112, 'For those who are willing to make an effort, great miracles and wonderful treasures are in store.', 1467, 0), (470113, 'When small men attempt great enterprises, they always end by reducing them to the level of their mediocrity.', 1702, 0), (470114, 'For me, it''s a great thing to tell people anything is possible. When I was 15, people told me ''You''re not going to be a DJ.''', 69269, 0), (470115, 'I always seem to get inspiration and renewed vitality by contact with this great novel land of yours which sticks up out of the Atlantic.', 3621, 0), (470116, 'A great man is a torch in the darkness, a beacon in superstition''s night, an inspiration and a prophecy.', 67335, 0), (470117, 'Above all things let us never forget that mankind constitutes one great brotherhood; all born to encounter suffering and sorrow, and therefore bound to sympathize with each other.', 2076, 0), (470118, 'It was great. I mean, it''s a blast directing underwater stuff.', 74189, 0), (470119, 'The Jews don''t like Farrakhan, so they call me Hitler. Well, that''s a good name. Hitler was a very great man.', 51994, 0), (470120, 'Though I do not believe that a plant will spring up where no seed has been, I have great faith in a seed... Convince me that you have a seed there, and I am prepared to expect wonders.', 1049, 0), (470121, 'Character may be manifested in the great moments, but it is made in the small ones.', 22130, 0), (470122, 'We are all one - or at least we should be - and it is our job, our duty, and our great challenge to fight the voices of division and seek the salve of reconciliation.', 70990, 0), (470123, 'Only passions, great passions can elevate the soul to great things.', 2879, 0), (470124, 'It is of great importance to our country generally, and especially to our navigating and whaling interests, that the Pacific Coast and, indeed, the whole of our territory west of the Rocky Mountains, should speedily be filled up by a hardy and patriotic population.', 71937, 0), (470125, 'We are continually faced by great opportunities brilliantly disguised as insoluble problems.', 11247, 0), (470126, 'The old days were the old days. And they were great days. But now is now.', 53024, 0), (470127, 'I do what I do. You like it, great. You don''t, go listen to somebody else. I''m stickin'' with the people who stuck with me.', 26404, 0), (470128, 'If you''re sitting in your minivan, playing your computer animated films for your children in the back seat, is it the animation that''s entertaining you as you drive and listen? No, it''s the storytelling. That''s why we put so much importance on story. No amount of great animation will save a bad story.', 68139, 0), (470129, 'Great leaders help their people see how they can directly impact the company''s objectives and their own personal goals.', 69536, 0), (470130, 'I had great relationship with the Hispanic - we had a lot of Hispanics in the school actually from different countries, Venezuela, from Brazil, and they all played soccer, and I was on the soccer team, and I developed great relationships with them.', 64643, 0), (470131, 'The atom bomb was no ''great decision.'' It was merely another powerful weapon in the arsenal of righteousness.', 16121, 0), (470132, 'Magic touches people in the way great art does. It lets them see the world with new eyes.', 74190, 0), (470133, 'Being pampered is great, but sometimes I like to do those things myself because it''s a little therapeutic and gives me some downtime for myself - and I need that.', 72302, 0), (470134, 'The key to the mystery of a great artist is that for reasons unknown, he will give away his energies and his life just to make sure that one note follows another... and leaves us with the feeling that something is right in the world.', 2229, 0), (470135, 'I looked back on the roaring Twenties, with its jazz, ''Great Gatsby'' and the pre-Code films as a party I had somehow managed to miss.', 38121, 0), (470136, 'Love of glory can only create a great hero contempt of glory creates a great man. ', 59960, 0), (470137, 'Whatever I have tried to do in life, I have tried with all my heart to do it well; whatever I have devoted myself to, I have devoted myself completely; in great aims and in small I have always thoroughly been in earnest.', 96, 0), (470138, 'There would be no great men if there were no little ones.', 3428, 0), (470139, 'Great things are won by great dangers.', 1863, 0), (470140, 'He who would accomplish little must sacrifice little he who would achieve much must sacrifice much he who would attain highly must sacrifice greatly. ', 2970, 0), (470141, 'For the person for whom small things do not exist, the great is not great.', 2800, 0), (470142, 'The greater the effort, the greater the glory.', 3285, 0), (470143, 'Great wisdom is generous; petty wisdom is contentious. Great speech is impassioned, small speech cantankerous.', 2480, 0), (470144, 'And the American people are the greatest people in the world. What makes America the greatest nation in the world is the heart of the American people: hardworking, innovative, risk-taking, God- loving, family-oriented American people.', 52321, 0), (470145, 'We grow small trying to be great.', 14620, 0), (470146, 'I call upon the scientific community in our country, those who gave us nuclear weapons, to turn their great talents now to the cause of mankind and world peace: to give us the means of rendering these nuclear weapons impotent and obsolete.', 1727, 0), (470147, 'During the Great Depression, levels of crime actually dropped. During the 1920s, when life was free and easy, so was crime. During the 1930s, when the entire American economy fell into a government-owned alligator moat, crime was nearly non-existent. During the 1950s and 1960s, when the economy was excellent, crime rose again.', 17797, 0), (470148, 'What makes America great is that we can come together during times of national tragedy.', 71162, 0), (470149, 'Miami is one of these great places that is a really sensual, physically beautiful place.', 72144, 0), (470150, 'I have known plenty of people who, in their later years, had the energy of children and the kind of curiosity and fascination with things like little children. I think we can keep that, and I think it''s important to keep that part of staying young. But I also think it''s great fun growing old.', 148, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (470151, 'Lesser artists borrow, great artists steal.', 16868, 0), (470152, 'You are that vast thing that you see far, far off with great telescopes.', 45466, 0), (470153, 'The measure of a man is not how great his faith is, but how great his love is. We must not let government programs disconnect our souls from each other.', 67449, 0), (470154, 'I have learned that nothing is certain except for the need to have strong risk management, a lot of cash, the willingness to invest even when the future is unclear, and great people.', 72017, 0), (470155, 'Helping people getting a great start in life, a great foundation, is an investment.', 72630, 0), (470156, 'It makes no difference how deeply seated may be the trouble, how hopeless the outlook how muddled the tangle, how great the mistake. A sufficient realization of love will dissolve it all.', 357, 0), (470157, 'A great opera house isn''t run by a director, but by a great administrator.', 74191, 0), (470158, 'Enlightenment is always there. Small enlightenment will bring great enlightenment. If you breathe in and are aware that you are alive - that you can touch the miracle of being alive - then that is a kind of enlightenment.', 394, 0), (470159, 'I like bowling. I suck at it, but I like it. You know what''s so funny? I have days when I''m absolutely great at doing it, and then I have days when I just don''t understand it.', 67665, 0), (470160, 'I always try to start my weekend by running on the beach, which is great fun here in Barcelona.', 72625, 0), (470161, 'We are domesticated animals, revolving in a cage which we have built for ourselves - with its contentions, wranglings, its impossible political leaders, its gurus who exploit our self-conceit and their own with great refinement or rather crudely.', 1780, 0), (470162, 'Every great brand is like a great story.', 67039, 0), (470163, 'Forgive, O Lord, my little jokes on Thee, and I''ll forgive Thy great big joke on me.', 35, 0), (470164, 'A subtle thought that is in error may yet give rise to fruitful inquiry that can establish truths of great value.', 988, 0), (470165, 'When you talk about a great actor, you''re not talking about Tom Cruise. His whole behavior is so shocking. It''s inappropriate and vulgar and absolutely unacceptable to use your private life to sell anything commercially, but I think it''s kind of a sickness.', 12702, 0), (470166, 'A book has got smell. A new book smells great. An old book smells even better. An old book smells like ancient Egypt.', 567, 0), (470167, 'I have a great relationship with my mother-in-law. We''re both Leos, we understand each other.', 1549, 0), (470168, 'One of the great questions of philosophy is, do we innately have morality, or do we get it from celestial dictation? A study of the Ten Commandments is a very good way of getting into and resolving that issue.', 1188, 0), (470169, 'I''m all about showing people that I''m a little messed up, I have a lot of the same problems you have. By exposing myself and putting myself out there, people can relate to me and my act won''t grow stale. I mean, nobody wants to hear a comedian say, ''Life is great.''', 69696, 0), (470170, 'Jamaica''s a country of great dichotomy. On the one hand you have a tourist industry with great beaches and resorts, but on the other you have such great poverty and the violence that goes along with that.', 21674, 0), (470171, 'The difference between Marilyn Monroe and the early Pamela Anderson is not that great.', 38121, 0), (470172, 'The wicked leader is he who the people despise. The good leader is he who the people revere. The great leader is he who the people say, ''We did it ourselves.''', 15, 0), (470173, 'Trouble is the common denominator of living. It is the great equalizer.', 3131, 0), (470174, 'Never forget that no military leader has ever become great without audacity.', 2677, 0), (470175, 'A great novel is concerned primarily with the interior 