, 'We are not for disarming people. When you have an epidemic it''s a public health issue, a safety issue.', 74230, 0), (470616, 'Meat consumption is just as dangerous to public health as tobacco use... It''s time we looked into holding the meat producers and fast-food outlets legally accountable.', 72741, 0), (470617, 'People are at their happiest if they are true to themselves. I think that applies to their chosen profession, friends and relationships. It goes for your health too. If you are true to yourself, it seems to me everything should work out pretty well.', 74231, 0), (470618, 'I don''t think there''s a shortage of material in the world. Or in my head. I just pray for continued good health, because I''ve got other stories to tell.', 8957, 0), (470619, 'As problems like identity theft become more prevalent, now more than ever, Americans need to take their financial health seriously - and this information is of the utmost importance.', 70459, 0), (470620, 'The old problems - love, money, security, status, health, etc. - are still here to plague us or please us.', 68617, 0), (470621, 'But if you''re asking my opinion, I would argue that a social justice approach should be central to medicine and utilized to be central to public health. This could be very simple: the well should take care of the sick.', 13377, 0), (470622, 'Man becomes weak or ill by accident as a consequence of the lack of resources. Even the most severally ill patients must be treated with the aim of restoring their health.', 74157, 0), (470623, 'We drink one another''s health and spoil our own.', 2174, 0), (470624, 'In health there is freedom. Health is the first of all liberties.', 4754, 0), (470625, 'The U.S. routinely ranks lower than other countries in health outcomes such as infant mortality.', 74232, 0), (470626, 'The same things that lead to disparities in health in this country on a day-to-day basis led to disparities in the impact of Hurricane Katrina.', 74233, 0), (470627, 'Reconciliation cannot be used to pass comprehensive health care reform. It won''t work because it was never designed for that kind of significant legislation it was designed for deficit reduction. ', 70119, 0), (470628, 'If we do nothing, as the Republicans suggest, we''re going to see health care costs reach a point where small businesses can''t afford it and families can''t afford it. We''re going to see people turned down from pre-existing conditions. We''re going to find the Medicare doughnut hole - a gap in coverage that''s going to hurt a lot of seniors.', 74234, 0), (470629, 'We will have health care reform in America.', 74234, 0), (470630, 'But if you - if what - the reports are true, what they''re saying is, is that as a consequence of us getting 30 million additional people health care, at the margins that''s going to increase our costs, we knew that.', 1693, 0), (470631, 'It''s never too late to take your heart health seriously and make it a priority.', 71070, 0), (470632, 'The truth is I had lots of rehab and now I have a clean bill of health.', 70721, 0), (470633, 'We are spending most of our time in American health care fixing the mistakes that either we in the profession are causing or our patients are, without recognizing it, causing to themselves.', 72135, 0), (470634, 'No matter how old you are, no matter how much you weigh, you can still control the health of your body.', 72135, 0), (470635, 'I should do something about the cigarettes; I quite accept that it''s bad for your health, but you know a moderate tipple is positively beneficial and, at certain times, absolutely essential.', 63093, 0), (470636, 'It was a simple question any employee should ask: ''Oh and by the way, how do I get my health insurance to be seamless?''', 74227, 0), (470637, 'When a woman earns a dollar, the payback is higher. She''ll invest in her children, in their education, health care, and basic needs. The impact of a woman''s role in the economy benefits society at large.', 666