are to isolated farm and mountain areas. They recommended to do that partly by deploying trained nurse practitioners in places with no doctors to provide primary care they were trained to provide.', 17805, 0), (470819, 'No one wants to fail. So most of us don''t even try. Sad. We don''t even take that first step to improve our health or to deepen our working relationships or to realize a dream.', 1172, 0), (470820, 'While Democrats fussed with the details of health care reforms, conservatives spent months telling the nation that the real issue is freedom, that what''s on the line is American liberty itself.', 11636, 0), (470821, 'We control health and pathogenicity by complex multi-speciated relationships through symbiosis and synergy. Portable shelters for livestock, along with electric fencing, insure hygienic and sanitary housing and lounging areas, not to mention clean air, sunshine, and exercise.', 2536, 0), (470822, 'As women slowly gain power, their values and priorities are reshaping the agenda. A multitude of studies show that when women control the family funds, they generally spend more on health, nutrition, and education - and less on alcohol and cigarettes.', 68451, 0), (470823, 'Our message of ensuring every Hoosier has access to a quality education that turns into a good paying job, that ultimately leads to a meaningful career with access to affordable health care, is resonating.', 72129, 0), (470824, 'The root cause of the looming energy problem - and the key to easing environmental, economic and religious tensions while improving public health - is to address the unending, and unequal, growth of the human population. And the one proven way to reduce fertility rates is to empower young women by educating them.', 1129, 0), (470825, 'Laziness works. And the simple way to incorporate its health benefits into your life is simply to take a nap.', 16461, 0), (470826, 'Today there are people trying to take away rights that our mothers, grandmothers and grea