ewhere that when a person takes part in community action, his health improves. Something happens to him or to her biologically. It''s like a tonic.', 16129, 0), (470922, 'Health has always been an important thing to me. I exercise and try to take care of myself, and drink a lot of water! And I push that to my kids so that they can carry on that same energy.', 67916, 0), (470923, 'Health is never going to go out of fashion.', 69253, 0), (470924, 'To protect our country''s economic future and the health and well being of all Americans, we must find a way to rein in out-of-control costs, provide quality, affordable health care choices to all, and make outrageous insurance industry abuses a thing of the past.', 71032, 0), (470925, 'How do you deliver the best possible and affordable health care to maximize health?', 74213, 0), (470926, 'Trying to maintain your health on the road can be difficult. Especially in the middle of the country where they close by 9 and you''re not out of work until midnight. You end up at a McDonald''s or Taco Bell.', 74244, 0), (470927, 'Contraceptives have a proven track record of enhancing the health of women and children, preventing unintended pregnancy, and reducing the need for abortion.', 72267, 0), (470928, 'India remains one of the few nations which still focuses entirely on an archaic de-addiction model, administered by the ministry of social justice and empowerment, to address drinking problems, adhering to a centuries-old idea of these problems being a moral disorder rather than a health condition.', 66569, 0), (470929, 'I am now almost certain that we need more radiation for better health.', 73570, 0), (470930, 'I''ve made a promise to myself to be a 100% healthy person if nothing else.', 54969, 0), (470931, 'The biggest mistakes, early on, involved foreign policy and involved the strategy for health care.', 74245, 0), (470932, 'The great equalizer is health. If you don''t have it, you''re screwed.', 68582, 0), (470933, 'We seek to protect and preserve life for life''s own sake in everything from our most fundamental laws of homicide to our road traffic regulations to our largest governmental programs for health and social security.', 66620, 0), (470934, 'I believe that if you''re healthy, you''re capable of doing everything. There''s no one else who can give you health but God, and by being healthy I believe that God is listening to me.', 67926, 0), (470935, 'From exam grading to health education to professional training to democratic participation, paths towards self-realization and success in the world are often daunting and obscure: journeys only the privileged feel confident setting off along.', 49929, 0), (470936, 'Like health care, education is something worth spending on and worth investing in, but we''re spending more and getting less.', 70109, 0), (470937, 'I have a great race team, great grew members, awesome health care team, endocrinologist, nutritionist, and of course family and friends. It truly is a team effort, both when you are dealing with diabetes in regular life and also on the racetrack.', 72031, 0), (470938, 'People have criticized me for seeming to step out of my professional role to become undignifiedly political. I''d say it was belated realization that day care, good schools, health insurance, and nuclear disarmament are even more important aspects of pediatrics than measles vaccine or vitamin D.', 2463, 0), (470939, 'If I have my health I can carry on. There will be a point when I do quit but I have absolutely no idea when that is.', 59447, 0), (470940, 'There''s definitely evidence that capitalism at its most ruthless rewards psychopathic behavior. When you look at the worst corners of the American health insurance industry or the sub-prime banking market, it really feels like the more psychopathically someone behaves, the more it''s rewarded.', 1846, 0), (470941, 'We''ve got to have major health care reform because that is the 800-pound gorilla. That is the thing that can swamp the boat fiscally for the United States.', 70119, 0), (470942, 'I don''t know what these Republican congressmen drink that make them experts on women''s reproductive health.', 72885, 0), (470943, 'Everyone knows that exercise can improve your health. Exercise is a key part of managing your weight and maintaining healthy hearts, lungs, and other bodily systems. But did you know that exercise can make you more productive? The latest research shows that a regular exercise routine can make you happier, smarter, and more energetic.', 74246, 0), (470944, 'We need a vibrant Medicaid program and strategies to expand affordable access to health care for all, especially for the specialty care services that community health centers do not provide.', 73983, 0), (470945, 'Taking notes at a pub in Salisbury, I was mistaken for a health inspector!', 2314, 0), (470946, 'It''s okay to talk about birth, okay - then menstruation. I first started my advocacy for women''s health in the field of reproductive freedom, and the next stage would be bringing menopause out of the closet.', 73574, 0), (470947, 'Patients are empowered by having better access to their own health information, and then by owning their own data.', 74247, 0), (470948, 'The right to protect the health and well-being of every person, of those we love, is a basic human right.', 74247, 0), (470949, 'The quarterback is the most vulnerable one on the field. He''s in an awkward position a lot of times when he throws the ball. So he does have to be protected. You lose a quarterback, you''re in trouble. I don''t know if they can make it too safe. I think health becomes an issue.', 69718, 0), (470950, 'People are going to be living quite soon for 100 years. Our idea of how a family works no longer applies. It''s no good saying you''re going to have children for 15 years and then you''re going to retire and have hobbies, because you''ve got 40 more years to go after 60 and you''re in good health until 90 or some