ll force government in Canada to approve complete health insurance.', 29501, 0), (470984, 'Pay mind to your own life, your own health, and wholeness. A bleeding heart is of no help to anyone if it bleeds to death.', 899, 0), (470985, 'Health and beauty is not just about what you apply. If you don''t have it together on the inside, then nothing else is going to matter.', 74256, 0), (470986, 'I feel pretty good. My body actually looks like an old banana, but it''s fine.', 68151, 0), (470987, 'Our health care system squanders money because it is designed to react to emergencies. Homeless shelters, hospital emergency rooms, jails, prisons - these are expensive and ineffective ways to intervene and there are people who clearly profit from this cycle of continued suffering.', 61510, 0), (470988, 'We don''t come to Canada for our health. We can think of other ways of enjoying ourselves.', 64417, 0), (470989, 'A zombie amusement park sounds like fun, but the health code violations alone are enough to turn your stomach.', 10525, 0), (470990, 'I learned that people everywhere are basically the same and have similar goals that we do. They want health and happiness and the opportunity to provide for their families.', 74257, 0), (470991, 'There is actually a physical connection between light and our health and wellbeing.', 74258, 0), (470992, 'The first draught serveth for health, the second for pleasure, the third for shame, and the fourth for madness.', 62557, 0), (470993, 'If you''re not paying for it through the health plan, you pay for it in the emergency room.', 44582, 0), (470994, 'My whole professional life has been dedicated to improving access, affordability, quality and choice of health care.', 74259, 0), (470995, 'At FDA, our mission is to promote and protect the health of the public. As commissioner, I''ve worked hard to galvanize people around that idea. I want employees to be thinking about the unique and essential contribution they are making to our mission.', 73825, 0), (470996, 'My good health, coupled with joy of tobogganing and my desire to be the best, has helped me stay in professional sport for so long.', 74260, 0), (470997, 'I don''t want to suggest that controlling pharmaceutical costs is the answer to what ails the U.S. health care system. It isn''t.', 74261, 0), (470998, 'I think the most important thing in life is your health. If you haven''t got your health, you haven''t got anything.', 74262, 0), (470999, 'The world is a book, and those who do not travel read only a page.', 63060, 0), (471000, 'Success comes to those who dedicate everything to their passion in life. To be successful, it is also very important to be humble and never let fame or money travel to your head.', 66442, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471001, 'To travel is to take a journey into yourself.', 1181, 0), (471002, 'It is better to travel well than to arrive.', 63441, 0), (471003, 'Exploration is really the essence of the human spirit.', 46704, 0), (471004, 'I see my path, but I don''t know where it leads. Not knowing where I''m going is what inspires me to travel it.', 71931, 0), (471005, 'Travel early and travel often. Live abroad, if you can. Understand cultures other than your own. As your understanding of other cultures increases, your understanding of yourself and your own culture will increase exponentially.', 70575, 0), (471006, 'All journeys have secret destinations of which the traveler is unaware.', 1938, 0), (471007, 'A journey is a person in itself; no two are alike. And all plans, safeguards, policing, and coercion are fruitless. We find that after years of struggle that we do not take a trip; a trip takes us.', 1070, 0), (471008, 'The traveler sees what he sees, the tourist sees what he has come to see.', 67663, 0), (471009, 'If you want to succeed you should strike out on new paths, rather than travel the worn paths of accepted success.', 11161, 0), (471010, 'Travel can be one of the most rewarding forms of introspection.', 6034, 0), (471011, 'I am blessed for what I have, but I believed in it from the beginning. Today, the dream is the same: I still want to travel, I still want to entertain, and I most certainly still want to have fun.', 68163, 0), (471012, 'Travel becomes a strategy for accumulating photographs.', 4673, 0), (471013, 'We are what our thoughts have made us so take care about what you think. Words are secondary. Thoughts live they travel far. ', 1838, 0), (471014, 'Riding a bicycle is the summit of human endeavour - an almost neutral environmental effect coupled with the ability to travel substantial distances without disturbing anybody. The bike is the perfect marriage of technology and human energy.', 50602, 0), (471015, 'For once you have tasted flight you will walk the earth with your eyes turned skywards, for there you have been and there you will long to return.', 1386, 0), (471016, 'Own only what you can always carry with you: know languages, know countries, know people. Let your memory be your travel bag.', 2564, 0), (471017, 'We must go beyond textbooks, go out into the bypaths and untrodden depths of the wilderness and travel and explore and tell the world the glories of our journey.', 18525, 0), (471018, 'Rome is the city of echoes, the city of illusions, and the city of yearning.', 32709, 0), (471019, 'If one had but a single glance to give the world, one should gaze on Istanbul.', 3430, 0), (471020, 'I would travel only by horse, if I had the choice.', 52060, 0), (471021, 'To travel is to discover that everyone is wrong about other countries.', 1032, 0), (471022, 'Travelling expands the mind rarely.', 1113, 0), (471023, 'The world is getting more connected through technology and travel. Cuisines are evolving. Some people are scared of globalization, but I think people will always take pride in cultural heritage.', 66656, 0), (471024, 'I travel around the world, and there are so many beautiful girls, but that''s not going to make you a supermodel. You have to have something more than just a pretty face.', 67736, 0), (471025, 'If all difficulties were known at the outset of a long journey, most of us would never start out at all.', 12782, 0), (471026, 'Ah! Young people, travel if you can, and if you cannot - travel all the same!', 3205, 0), (471027, 'One travels more usefully when alone, because he reflects more.', 1207, 0), (471028, 'I''ve just concluded - since President Obama endorses the same-sex marriage, advocates homosexual people, and enjoys an attractive countenance - thus if it becomes necessary, I shall travel to Washington, D.C., get down on my knee, and ask his hand.', 32803, 0), (471029, 'The travel and tourism industry, it''s just a huge part of our economy.', 68392, 0), (471030, 'To the lover of wilderness, Alaska is one of the most wonderful countries in the world.', 1402, 0), (471031, 'One of my passions is photography. I always carry a camera in my bag whenever I travel. I always take pictures wherever I go, and some of them end up being really crazy ones.', 74263, 0), (471032, 'The person attempting to travel two roads at once will get nowhere.', 46458, 0), (471033, 'The world is getting so small. Young people are mobile; they want to travel around the world. When you travel around the world, you exchange culture, you want to make friends, you want to exchange things.', 66598, 0), (471034, 'Travel teaches as much as books.', 67136, 0), (471035, 'Even if you can''t afford to travel the world, you can take your children to the museum, zoo or local park. And don''t be afraid to take them to grown-up spots. Eating out in a restaurant teaches children how to be quiet and polite and gives them the pleasure of knowing you trust them to behave.', 69226, 0), (471036, 'If you wish to travel far and fast, travel light. Take off all your envies, jealousies, unforgiveness, selfishness and fears.', 1078, 0), (471037, 'Venice is like eating an entire box of chocolate liqueurs in one go.', 262, 0), (471038, 'The land created me. I''m wild and lonesome. Even as I travel the cities, I''m more at home in the vacant lots.', 289, 0), (471039, 'I love to travel, but hate to arrive.', 68683, 0), (471040, 'A good story can travel in time and borders it hits you no matter where you are. ', 43090, 0), (471041, 'Think Indonesia and tourism, and the first thing that comes to mind is probably Bali. Think golf holiday, and most people would dream of Scotland or Ireland. But Indonesia harbors one of the best-kept secrets in the world of travel: it is a golfer''s paradise.', 74264, 0), (471042, 'And, obviously as a, as one who likes to travel around myself a lot, I think the Earth is a beautiful place. And, I''m looking forward to some new perspectives.', 69886, 0), (471043, 'Time travel is such a magic concept.', 1346, 0), (471044, 'The world reveals itself to those who travel on foot.', 2043, 0), (471045, 'The secret to modern life is finding the measure in time management. I have two kids, career and I travel, and I don''t think my life is any different than most couples. The most valuable commodity now for many people is time and how to parcel that out.', 43985, 0), (471046, 'Taking time to sit back and watch and think about what you''ve seen is important. Traveling did a great deal to me. I found that when I travel and just sit in the corner and watch, a million ideas come to me.', 70737, 0), (471047, 'I love to photograph the gorgeous landscapes when I travel.', 38496, 0), (471048, 'The first condition of understanding a foreign country is to smell it.', 843, 0), (471049, 'People don''t understand that where I come from, everyone is either a convict, been in jail, been in a gang, is a hooligan of some sorts, but those are my brothers, my family and the people that I travel with. Those are the people that I roll with.', 68942, 0), (471050, 'I have no problem with the adventure travel movement. It makes better, more sensitive people. If you get people diving on a coral reef, they''re going to become more respectful of the outdoors and more concerned with the threats that places like that face and they''re going to care more about protecting them than they would have before.', 26945, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471051, 'The everyday kindness of the back roads more than makes up for the acts of greed in the headlines.', 37230, 0), (471052, 'Certainly, travel is more than the seeing of sights; it is a change that goes on, deep and permanent, in the ideas of living.', 64286, 0), (471053, 'Travel is a lot like love.', 639, 0), (471054, 'Let me be a free man - free to travel, free to stop, free to work.', 4664, 0), (471055, 'I love the simplicity, the ingredients, the culture, the history and the seasonality of Italian cuisine. In Italy people do not travel. They cook the way grandma did, using fresh ingredients and what is available in season.', 66701, 0), (471056, 'No one realizes how beautiful it is to travel until he comes home and rests his head on his old, familiar pillow.', 1317, 0), (471057, 'I love single life! Why would it be boring? I mean, I get to travel around and have loads of girls screaming at me, so it''s definitely not boring. However, it can get lonely on the road, but I''m sorted I''ve got good people around me.', 68956, 0), (471058, 'When I travel, I feel more like a nomad than a tourist.', 5980, 0), (471059, 'As I get older, the things that I want are starting to make more sense. Being able to travel makes me happy, and I am a person that lives in the moment. I also want to live a good life. Traveling makes everyday issues seem so much smaller and really changes my perspective on things.', 72993, 0), (471060, 'No one can travel your own road for you you must travel it for yourself. My faith in this stems from my childhood. I grew up in a family with a system of religious beliefs handed down to me. ', 1039, 0), (471061, 'Songs really are like a form of time travel because they really have moved forward in a bubble. Everyone who''s connected with it, the studio''s gone, the musicians are gone, and the only thing that''s left is this recording which was only about a three-minute period maybe 70 years ago.', 2201, 0), (471062, 'During their service, men and women in our Armed Forces live by a common creed, promising never to leave a soldier behind. We should live by the same principle. When our veterans are asked to travel hundreds of miles for care that''s offered right next door, we simply aren''t living up to that standard, and something has to change.', 71180, 0), (471063, 'I am sort of an adventurer. I like to explore new places. I don''t get to travel as often as I would like but I love it.', 74265, 0), (471064, 'How often I found where I should be going only by setting out for somewhere else.', 11496, 0), (471065, 'People commonly travel the world over to see rivers and mountains, new stars, garish birds, freak fish, grotesque breeds of human; they fall into an animal stupor that gapes at existence and they think they have seen something.', 3131, 0), (471066, 'When I''m home, I spend Sunday with my husband. If we''re not cooking, we travel around in our camper, stop at fast-food restaurants, and picnic. We love that stuff that will harden your arteries in a hurry.', 1300, 0), (471067, 'We would go back and maybe not say that thing to our dad that we said, or maybe be a little nicer to someone who we cared about and had a relationship with when we were young. You know, they''re subtle things, but we carry those with us forever. And I think that regret and time travel are intrinsically linked to me.', 74266, 0), (471068, 'I have wandered all my life, and I have also traveled; the difference between the two being this, that we wander for distraction, but we travel for fulfillment.', 4439, 0), (471069, 'I would wear the blue overalls of the fieldworker and often wore round, rimless glasses known as Mazzawati teaglasses. I had a car, and I wore a chauffeur''s cap with my overalls. The pose of chauffeur was convenient because I could travel under the pretext of driving my master''s car.', 1722, 0), (471070, 'I want my handbags and my shoes to be stylish but I want to make sure that they''re versatile. I travel and I have to make sure the pieces I put into my bag can go with a dress or with shorts or jeans.', 68355, 0), (471071, 'I find the whole time travel question very unsettling if you take it to its logical extension. I think it might eventually be possible, but then what happens?', 30037, 0), (471072, 'I am living out my adolescent dream of travel and adventure.', 26945, 0), (471073, 'I travel in so many different ways; I travel high, I rough it... it all depends on who I travel with.', 1088, 0), (471074, 'I want to travel. Maybe I''ll end up living in Norway, making cakes.', 68128, 0), (471075, 'I enjoy the preparatory elements of travel - packing my bags and choosing my outfits - but my favourite part is getting there.', 45050, 0), (471076, 'I travel so much on stories, so I don''t take vacation much, but one place I go back to again and again is my ranch.', 67652, 0), (471077, 'I get very homesick, but otherwise it''s a great privilege to get to travel for work.', 14544, 0), (471078, 'The way that people feel changes everything. Feelings are forces. They cause us to time travel. And to leave ourselves, to leave our bodies. I would be that kind of psychologist who says, ''You''re absolutely right - there are monsters under the bed.''', 9941, 0), (471079, 'To be a Christian who is willing to travel with Christ on his downward road requires being willing to detach oneself constantly from any need to be relevant, and to trust ever more deeply the Word of God.', 19097, 0), (471080, 'Know how to travel from your town to a nearby town without a car, either by bus or by rail.', 814, 0), (471081, 'In Italy, they add work and life on to food and wine.', 66645, 0), (471082, 'In our town, Halloween was terrifying and thrilling, and there was a whiff of homicide. We''d travel by foot in the dark for miles, collecting candy, watching out for adults who seemed too eager to give us treats.', 15862, 0), (471083, 'The traveller has reached the end of the journey!', 2026, 0), (471084, 'Tourists don''t know where they''ve been, travelers don''t know where they''re going.', 1979, 0), (471085, 'He travels the fastest who travels alone.', 843, 0), (471086, 'You get educated by traveling.', 69212, 0), (471087, 'I wanted to travel from the beginning. As a kid, I used to dream about airplanes, before I ever flew in one.', 68218, 0), (471088, 'Everywhere is nowhere. When a person spends all his time in foreign travel, he ends by having many acquaintances, but no friends.', 65434, 0), (471089, 'To travel hopefully is a better thing than to arrive.', 449, 0), (471090, 'The bottom line is that time travel is allowed by the laws of physics.', 3476, 0), (471091, 'Many years ago, large packs of wolves roamed the countryside in Ukraine, making travel in that part of the world very dangerous. These wolf packs were fearless. They were not intimidated by people nor by any of the weapons available at that time. The only thing that seemed to frighten them was fire.', 4294, 0), (471092, 'In all my wild mountaineering, I have enjoyed only one avalanche ride; and the start was so sudden, and the end came so soon, I thought but little of the danger that goes with this sort of travel, though one thinks fast at such times.', 1402, 0), (471093, 'Travel works best when you''re forced to come to terms with the place you''re in.', 1979, 0), (471094, 'There''s no such thing as a specific authenticity to what Mexico is, because Mexico is incredibly complex and varied, and the food is completely different if you travel 50 kilometers. It just changes all the time.', 67800, 0), (471095, 'Travel, which was once either a necessity or an adventure, has become very largely a commodity, and from all sides we are persuaded into thinking that it is a social requirement, too.', 37235, 0), (471096, 'Spontaneity is what travel is all about.', 68492, 0), (471097, 'Some people are drawn naturally - there are natural guitarists, and there are natural piano players, and I think guitar implies travel, a sort of footloose gypsy existence. You grab your bag and you go to the next town.', 5933, 0), (471098, 'You do not travel if you are afraid of the unknown, you travel for the unknown, that reveals you with yourself.', 70829, 0), (471099, 'If you''re successful, it''s important to enjoy it! I love shopping for clothes, branded clothes. I love shopping in England, Dubai. I like to travel whenever I can.', 67900, 0), (471100, 'The most useful form of time travel would be to go back a year or two and rectify the mistakes we made.', 74267, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471101, 'I love coming home to Melbourne. The first thing I do is have a coffee. It''s just so much better here than anywhere else. It''s better than in Italy and I travel a lot. I crave it.', 72668, 0), (471102, 'For many years, it seemed as if nothing changed in Norway. You could leave the country for three months, travel the world, through coups d''etat, assassinations, famines, massacres and tsunamis, and come home to find that the only new thing in the newspapers was the crossword puzzle.', 70724, 0), (471103, 'Working is actually a pleasure. It''s just very time-consuming. It''s a way of life. I find that I can work when I travel and work when I run. There is nothing like, on a rainy day, to work.', 67114, 0), (471104, 'Fitness is very important to me because it helps give me a routine when I travel. It gives me one hour of ''me'' time and passes the time when I''m lonely. Living with scoliosis serves as a constant reminder to keep my core and back strong. If I get lazy, I feel it in my back first.', 73841, 0), (471105, 'Immortality may be impossible, but imagine what humanity could learn if we all lived 700 years. We could travel deep into utopia and beyond.', 70518, 0), (471106, 'I travel a lot I hate having my life disrupted by routine. ', 74268, 0), (471107, 'It is for us to pray not for tasks equal to our powers, but for powers equal to our tasks, to go forward with a great desire forever beating at the door of our hearts as we travel toward our distant goal.', 701, 0), (471108, 'I get a friend to travel with me... I need somebody to bring me back to who I am. It''s hard to be alone.', 68700, 0), (471109, 'It always rains on tents. Rainstorms will travel thousands of miles, against prevailing winds for the opportunity to rain on a tent.', 2223, 0), (471110, 'Hurt leads to bitterness, bitterness to anger, travel too far that road and the way is lost.', 1943, 0), (471111, 'If you have enthusiasm, you have a very dynamic, effective companion to travel with you on the road to Somewhere.', 44815, 0), (471112, 'If somebody asked me about my inspiration I would say that it''s not the peopleand it''s not the things, it''s travel and experiencing different environments.', 69189, 0), (471113, 'Travel teaches toleration.', 1827, 0), (471114, 'I don''t have any superstitions, but what I always travel with is my pillow and my coffee.', 74269, 0), (471115, 'What I like in this job is you can travel to many places, many imaginations.', 61798, 0), (471116, 'I don''t feel restless, I just like to travel.', 2614, 0), (471117, 'Technologies that may be realized in centuries or millennium include: warp drive, traveling faster than the speed of light, parallel universes; are there other parallel dimensions and parallel realities? Time travel that we mentioned and going to the stars.', 1821, 0), (471118, 'One of the great things about music is that it has the capability of time travel - you smell a certain smell in the room and it takes you back to your childhood. I feel like music is able to do that, and it happens to me all the time.', 67810, 0), (471119, 'One of the few luxuries left is travel. And the aspect of travel that is luxurious is not the movement, but the being there.', 72661, 0), (471120, 'All the privileged can travel, see different worlds; not everyone can. I think it is important for people to have an interesting locale nearby.', 68727, 0), (471121, 'I do often fly first class, but I don''t travel with a posse, or bodyguard, or an assistant.', 11192, 0), (471122, 'I think that one of the main privileges of what I do, which I am just starting to learn, is to have the ability to travel all over the world and experience different cultures.', 49828, 0), (471123, 'I grew up in an era of thinking of travel as escape. The idea that you could conceivably have a new life, go somewhere, fall in love, have little children under the palm trees.', 1979, 0), (471124, 'What draws me in is that a trip is a leap in the dark. It''s like a metaphor for life. You set off from home, and in the classic travel book, you go to an unknown place. You discover a different world, and you discover yourself.', 1979, 0), (471125, 'The two impulses in travel are to get away from home, and the other is to pursue something - a landscape, people, an exotic place. Certainly finding a place that you like or discovering something unusual is a very sustaining thing in travel.', 1979, 0), (471126, 'I travel a lot, and I hunt for fabrics, then I have the tailor make me something.', 73066, 0), (471127, 'Touring is great because I love to travel.', 74270, 0), (471128, 'You can learn from everyone, the president or the cleaner. You need teachers in life, but they''re not always school teachers or professors. You learn from ordinary people. You learn from travel, from just walking down the street.', 74271, 0), (471129, 'I''ll bring my grits when I travel, because I get so hungry on the road.', 1300, 0), (471130, 'I travel with a bunch of battery packs because I don''t always have time to charge my phone at the hotel room when I''m traveling. I always change them, so I never run out of battery.', 74272, 0), (471131, 'The human voice: mysterious, spontaneous, primal. For me, the human voice is the vessel on which all emotions travel - except perhaps jealousy. And the breath, the breath is the captain of that vessel.', 74273, 0), (471132, 'People travel north from Barcelona, not south.', 67848, 0), (471133, 'When I was a kid, dressing right and looking good was a priority. As I grew up, I just wanted to stay that way, stick out a bit and have my own thing. That''s where white belts and wearing some colors started. So signing with Puma was a great fit for me. I usually travel with nine pairs of golf shoes and 10 belts.', 66920, 0), (471134, 'I try to lead a pretty active lifestyle. My biggest hobby is traveling with my family. I love to travel to new places and try crazy things. I''m a bit of a daredevil, so I have done things like zip lining, parasailing, scuba diving, and reverse bungee jumping!', 70225, 0), (471135, 'Time travel offends our sense of cause and effect - but maybe the universe doesn''t insist on cause and effect.', 72174, 0), (471136, 'I had time with my mother, but I really lived with my father. One time he gave all his salary so I could travel to a training camp. He couldn''t pay the rent, but he did that.', 69747, 0), (471137, 'I''m not proud of it, but I''m a great liar when I travel. I smile and lie, and things are smooth.', 9628, 0), (471138, 'We need to protect our wilderness areas and national parks. Everywhere you travel, you see blight, denuded mountains, logging. If people know what''s going on, they''ll become activists to safeguard those places.', 63466, 0), (471139, 'Radicals must be resilient, adaptable to shifting political circumstances, and sensitive enough to the process of action and reaction to avoid being trapped by their own tactics and forced to travel a road not of their choosing. In short, radicals must have a degree of control over the flow of events.', 48660, 0), (471140, 'You learn so much about yourself as an artist. I never would have thought that I could sing every night, you know? Travel and perform every single night, and travel to another city the next day and do it all over again? You learn a lot of new things about yourself, and you make a lot of connections with people.', 69351, 0), (471141, 'No matter where I travel, I make sure to carry a Vaseline body lotion with me to keep my skin well moisturised all the time.', 68008, 0), (471142, 'When I was drafted to Smackdown, I was like, ''Hell yes, I''m going to captain this ship.'' Then I was like, ''Oh, wait, you''re losing your best friend and travel partner and the person you enjoy having matches with the absolute most.'' That''s Charlotte. We travel together, and she is my best friend.', 69237, 0), (471143, 'I love listening to music on holiday, and back in the old days, I used to travel with cassette tapes and a boombox.', 74274, 0), (471144, 'Your lost friends are not dead, but gone before, advanced a stage or two upon that road which you must travel in the steps they trod.', 2600, 0), (471145, 'The world has become more complex as technology and easy travel mixes cultures without homogenizing them.', 25104, 0), (471146, 'We travel to learn; and I have never been in any country where they did not do something better than we do it, think some thoughts better than we think, catch some inspiration from heights above our own.', 6136, 0), (471147, 'The social issues outside of football are not as defined as they were earlier, when integration took place and certain rights were legislated. The Civil Rights movement is over. Individuals can buy homes wherever they want, travel first class wherever they want, eat wherever they want.', 67019, 0), (471148, 'Travel is so important in its capacity to expand the mind. It''s exciting to start as young as possible - you get to see how other cultures live, challenge your senses, and try different cuisines.', 69331, 0), (471149, 'Connecting with people, getting things done - that''s what makes the travel worthwhile.', 74275, 0), (471150, 'Yeah, yeah, yeah, time travel''s a nightmare. Don''t go down that path.', 68286, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471151, 'I think young people should travel and travel often to other countries... like I do.', 68, 0), (471152, 'If you have a fear of flying, don''t. The data are very clear: If you have to travel someplace, the safest way is by airplane.', 66565, 0), (471153, 'We''ve gotta reinvest in space travel. We should''ve never left the moon.', 567, 0), (471154, 'Travel is one of the best anti-war weapons that there are. I''ve been to Iran, and if you''re there you see little kids, cops, old people, cemeteries. Once you see that, you can''t say, ''Oh, Iran, let''s bomb them.''', 2042, 0), (471155, 'I need to travel, of course, with my laptop, so I can do my business on the road.', 67009, 0), (471156, 'Acting helped me as I was growing up. It helped me learn about myself, helped me travel, helped me understand life, express myself, all those wonderful things. So I''m very, very grateful; it''s a fun job. It''s a luxury.', 1380, 0), (471157, 'If you travel to Germany, it''s still absolutely Germany. If you travel to Sweden, it still has a Swedish identity.', 1259, 0), (471158, 'I travel regularly and have learnt to be very methodical as far as packing is concerned. For example, I always check the weather in advance of where I''m going to ensure that I''ve packed the right clothes.', 69336, 0), (471159, 'I always tell people, ''The music''s free. I get paid to travel.''', 66588, 0), (471160, 'It doesn''t matter if you''re a man or a woman - stay alert and focused on your surroundings. Travel with friends. Know where you are at all times, and never let your guard down.', 67858, 0), (471161, 'The thing about Hemingway that people forget is that all the stuff he did was at a time where people weren''t traveling that much. At 19 he travels to Italy. He goes to the Spanish Civil War. He goes to China, he goes to Africa so at that time to travel that much is really incredible.', 69136, 0), (471162, 'I think the most romantic thing you can do is just turn up. Turn up when it''s difficult for you. Travel halfway around the world or just up the road. Whatever it is, just be there.', 70221, 0), (471163, 'I don''t really desire things. I prefer to spend my money on experiences, on meals or travel.', 60126, 0), (471164, 'When I think, where did I laugh the most, where did I eat the most, where did I just feel good all the time, I would say making the Bond movie ''Die Another Day.'' To be part of such an iconic franchise and to travel to exotic places - that was the most fun I ever had.', 69081, 0), (471165, 'We didn''t travel much when I was little - most of what we did was visit various campsites around Conway, north Wales. My first major holiday abroad was to Ibiza with my parents when I was five. I vividly remember the plane touching down and that the hotel had great swings with lots of little lizards darting about that I was determined to catch.', 69750, 0), (471166, 'It''s been a huge blessing, being able to travel and have a great life.', 68360, 0), (471167, 'We travel so much, I never adjust to time zones any more.', 70682, 0), (471168, 'I''d love to travel to the Holy Land.', 28482, 0), (471169, 'If I have to travel, I''m going to travel my way and travel in the real world. And I''m going to have conversations every day with people in rest stops and people in gas stations and people in hotels and diners. That nourishes me.', 2131, 0), (471170, 'I grew up in South Africa and I would look at maps and we were at the bottom of the world. There was this whole thing up there. I was always reading encyclopedias about the world. So travel was something I was always attracted to.', 67513, 0), (471171, 'There comes a moment on a journey when something sweet, something irresistible and charming as wine raised to thirsty lips, wells up in the traveller''s being.', 74276, 0), (471172, 'Because it''s cheaper and easier to fly than ever before, air travel is becoming democratized.', 66565, 0), (471173, 'If you travel in time and space, most of the people you know and love will eventually be gone. But you''ll also be able to go and find them again.', 67557, 0), (471174, 'To be able to travel the world, especially to places I never thought I''d be... it''s really, you know, still fascinating for me.', 1525, 0), (471175, 'I travel without barely any luggage. Just a second set of underwear and binoculars and a map and a toothbrush.', 2043, 0), (471176, 'I love Ralph Lauren. As I travel so much, I prefer to shop online.', 69330, 0), (471177, 'We are not coaching on a daily basis because we often travel with our charity and commercial interests.', 14526, 0), (471178, 'When I travel, which is most of the year, I live in TripIt.', 68429, 0), (471179, 'Travel at least erodes some of the narrowness that exists in each of us.', 2553, 0), (471180, 'Every traveler knows too well the endless quest for the perfect travel bag: the one that''s stylish enough to carry through Paris, sturdy enough to tote around Peru, and - most important - doesn''t make your shoulder sag even before you''ve loaded it up with everything you need for a day of sightseeing.', 767, 0), (471181, 'I like to sit down, relax, have a cup of coffee on the terrace and read a book. I like to travel the world - and I''m lucky to see so much through cycling.', 68076, 0), (471182, 'Why, I''d like nothing better than to achieve some bold adventure, worthy of our trip.', 2600, 0), (471183, 'Travel in all the four quarters of the earth, yet you will find nothing anywhere. Whatever there is, is only here.', 4269, 0), (471184, 'People have to make journeys, what we want is people to have alternatives in public transport so that they can make a choice about the sort of way in which they''re going to travel.', 68838, 0), (471185, 'A good traveller is one who does not know where he is going to, and a perfect traveller does not know where he came from.', 1317, 0), (471186, 'Just got back from a pleasure trip: I took my mother-in-law to the airport.', 11800, 0), (471187, '''Closed timelike curve'' is the jargon for time travel. It means you go out, come back and meet yourself in the past.', 69846, 0), (471188, 'Dealing with global warming doesn''t mean we have all got to suddenly stop breathing. Dealing with global warming means that we have to stop waste, and if you travel for no reason whatsoever, that is a waste.', 3969, 0), (471189, 'While we celebrate our diversity, what surprises me time and time again as I travel around the constituency is that we are far more united and have far more in common with each other than things that divide us.', 73920, 0), (471190, 'London is a roost for every bird.', 1827, 0), (471191, 'Travel, for me, is a little bit like being in love because suddenly, all your senses are at the setting marked ''on.'' Suddenly, you''re alert to the secret patterns of the world.', 711, 0), (471192, 'The helicopter is a fine way to travel, but it induces a view of the world that only God and CEOs share on a regular basis.', 16319, 0), (471193, 'Everything becomes magnified at night. Sounds travel in a different way, it''s dark, and everything seems far more spooky.', 17159, 0), (471194, 'Travelers repose and dream among my leaves.', 221, 0), (471195, 'When the traveler goes alone he gets acquainted with himself.', 67479, 0), (471196, 'If you travel too often, you actually come face-to-face with what you''re trying to escape. I feel like when I travel alone, sometimes it''s like being locked in a hotel room with my own worst enemy.', 4035, 0), (471197, 'Travel like a pro, not like a hobo. That''s my motto.', 10679, 0), (471198, 'When the plane is delayed, it''s not the fault of the girl at the desk. I''m resigned to the fact that everything is out of my control and that air travel nowadays is barbaric.', 74277, 0), (471199, 'We take so many of our freedoms for granted nowadays - I can travel where I like, I can do any job I want - but I think chivalry has been lost a little bit.', 67438, 0), (471200, 'For my part, I travel not to go anywhere, but to go. I travel for travel''s sake. The great affair is to move.', 449, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471201, 'Don''t time travel into the past, roaming through the nuances as if they can change. Don''t bookmark pages you''ve already read.', 20595, 0), (471202, 'I''m not a big spender or shopper. Neither am I extravagant, nor do I have big expenses. I mainly spend on travel. I don''t buy overpriced clothes, as I feel such expenses are unnecessary. I probably wouldn''t buy expensive watches or jewellery either.', 66894, 0), (471203, 'Each and every one of the security measures we implement serves an important goal: providing safe and efficient air travel for the millions of people who rely on our aviation system every day.', 70324, 0), (471204, 'I grew up skateboarding; it was fun. I didn''t think about money, I didn''t know how much professional skateboarders made. I just knew that if I became a professional skateboarder, I would achieve a lot and get to travel and do these great things.', 69687, 0), (471205, 'I always like to arrive at the airport early to enjoy breakfast and lounge about so that when I get on the plane all my travel fever has disappeared.', 11190, 0), (471206, 'I don''t especially like to travel, not the way many people do. I know many people that love to go to far-off and different places, and I''ve never been like that. I seem to get homesick as quickly as a child.', 7241, 0), (471207, 'The Journey of Reconciliation was organized not only to devise techniques for eliminating Jim Crow in travel, but also as a training ground for similar peaceful projects against discrimination in such major areas as employment and in the armed services.', 51917, 0), (471208, 'Travel at faster than the speed of light certainly can have dramatic implications that are difficult to understand, such as time travel.', 58935, 0), (471209, 'Whenever possible, I use local, fresh ingredients, just because it tastes and feels better to eat an egg or a tomato or a hamburger that wasn''t flown halfway around the world, that didn''t travel on a truck and get stuck in traffic jams, that hasn''t been sitting in a supermarket''s refrigerator case for days.', 15511, 0), (471210, 'I really have created a family. I work with the people I love, I travel with them, I make films with them, and I''m in an office with them. So in a weird way - I know I haven''t birthed a child - I feel that I''m a part of creating a family. It''s a tribe. I love that word.', 292, 0), (471211, 'What does it mean to pre-board? Do you get on before you get on?', 1003, 0), (471212, 'People who don''t travel cannot have a global view, all they see is what''s in front of them. Those people cannot accept new things because all they know is where they live.', 71068, 0), (471213, 'Writing and travel broaden your ass if not your mind and I like to write standing up.', 110, 0), (471214, 'I think I am a travel junkie, and I have never enjoyed anything else in my life more than travelling and going to places.', 71872, 0), (471215, 'All travel has its advantages. If the passenger visits better countries, he may learn to improve his own. And if fortune carries him to worse, he may learn to enjoy it.', 2087, 0), (471216, 'I don''t mind where I work, it''s really nice to be able to travel around and taste the flavours of different countries.', 69083, 0), (471217, 'I am a passionate traveler, and from the time I was a child, travel formed me as much as my formal education. In order to appreciate cultures of another nation, one needs to go there, know the people and mingle with the culture of that country. One way to do that, if one is lucky enough, is to buy things from those cultures.', 73000, 0), (471218, 'Yeah. I''ve been pretty fortunate to travel I guess, all around the place.', 66775, 0), (471219, 'Tell people you''re a Canadian or a Kiwi when you travel and they''ll adore you.', 72704, 0), (471220, 'There was part of me that wanted to see the world and travel to distant places, but I could only do it in my imagination, so I read ferociously and imagined things.', 169, 0), (471221, 'Fifty years of isolating Cuba had failed to promote democracy, setting us back in Latin America. That''s why we restored diplomatic relations, opened the door to travel and commerce, and positioned ourselves to improve the lives of the Cuban people.', 1693, 0), (471222, 'Thursday night football is here to stay. So we''re looking at ways to make it safer. Now they''re playing division games, so you limit travel. Now the question is, should you play Sunday night before a Thursday night?', 13024, 0), (471223, 'I sit around listening to classical music. I don''t play video games. I love to go to dinner, go on picnics, travel.', 60732, 0), (471224, 'New York is the great stone desert.', 4298, 0), (471225, 'Travelers never think that they are the foreigners.', 12469, 0), (471226, 'You know more of a road by having traveled it than by all the conjectures and descriptions in the world.', 8948, 0), (471227, 'I never make a trip to the United States without visiting a supermarket. To me they are more fascinating than any fashion salon.', 62856, 0), (471228, 'Certain travellers give the impression that they keep moving because only then do they feel fully alive.', 70829, 0), (471229, 'You develop a sympathy for all human beings when you travel a lot.', 73523, 0), (471230, 'In this world, shipmates, sin that pays its way can travel freely, and without passport; whereas Virtue, if a pauper, is stopped at all frontiers.', 2584, 0), (471231, 'Travel is the most private of pleasures. There is no greater bore than the travel bore. We do not in the least want to hear what he has seen in Hong Kong.', 328, 0), (471232, 'Through travel I first became aware of the outside world it was through travel that I found my own introspective way into becoming a part of it. ', 1666, 0), (471233, 'Some minds improve by travel, others, rather, resemble copper wire, or brass, which get the narrower by going farther.', 21417, 0), (471234, 'I only travel to good material, a good director and a good company. I won''t work in another country for a year any longer, because I have a lovely wife and I adore her and I can''t bear to be away from her.', 74278, 0), (471235, 'Before the BBC, I joined the Navy in order to travel.', 3969, 0), (471236, 'My sisters and I were fortunate to travel through Asia and Europe at very young ages. We confronted extraordinary beauty in Athens and unspeakable poverty in India.', 74279, 0), (471237, 'Well, I took a sabbatical. I walked away from shooting movies because I couldn''t handle the travel. I''m a single parent. I had young kids, and I found that keeping in touch with them from hotel rooms and airports wasn''t working for me. So I stopped.', 72714, 0), (471238, 'A careful inspection showed them that, even if they succeeded in righting it by themselves, the cart would travel no longer. The axles were in a hopeless state, and the missing wheel was shattered into pieces.', 10296, 0), (471239, 'Besides, I''m a gypsy at heart and I like to travel around.', 1356, 0), (471240, 'I travel for work, but recently, friends said I should take major trips.', 74280, 0), (471241, 'I am traveling less in order to be able to write more. I select my travel destinations according to their degree of usefulness to my work.', 1357, 0), (471242, 'Travel, of course, narrows the mind.', 9186, 0), (471243, 'If you travel to the States... they have a lot of different words than like what we use. For instance: they say ''elevator'', we say ''lift''; they say ''drapes'', we say ''curtains''; they say ''president'', we say ''seriously deranged git.''', 17184, 0), (471244, 'Whenever I think of the high salaries we are paid as film actors, I think it is for the travel, the time away, and any trouble you get into through being well known. It''s not for the acting, that''s for sure.', 31358, 0), (471245, 'I''ve got a real sense of three-dimensional geometry. I can look at a flat piece of fabric and know that if I put a slit in it and make some fabric travel around a square, then when you lift it up it will drape in a certain way, and I can feel how that will happen.', 13967, 0), (471246, 'The amount of hassle involved in travel can be overwhelming.', 1979, 0), (471247, 'Southern political personalities, like sweet corn, travel badly. They lose flavor with every hundred yards away from the patch. By the time they reach New York, they are like Golden Bantam that has been trucked up from Texas - stale and unprofitable. The consumer forgets that the corn tastes different where it grows.', 9753, 0), (471248, 'As a person, I was born to give out my opinions. By giving out my opinions, I realize who I am. As long as I can communicate, I''m not so lonely. If I cannot travel, or do art, or have company, if they take away all my belongings, it doesn''t matter at all.', 20064, 0), (471249, 'My ideal travel companions are my surfboard, wetsuit, and guitar.', 74281, 0), (471250, 'I don''t like to leave anything unfinished on my desk before I travel.', 74282, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471251, 'Beyond racing, I just love the art form of running, of conceiving new ideas like the 50 Marathons in 50 States in 50 Days. It''s the ultimate expression of what I love to do, which is run, and travel, and see this great country.', 1615, 0), (471252, 'You can get too close as a team. You need time away from each other. You change in the same dressing room, you play on the same cricket field, you stay in the same hotel, you travel in the same planes and buses. C''mon - this business of everyone holding hands and being pally is nonsense.', 74283, 0), (471253, 'Each and every day, more people pay the price of Obamacare''s mountain of mandates. As I travel across the country, I continue to hear from Americans who want Washington to take its hands off of their healthcare.', 73044, 0), (471254, 'It never ceases to amaze me that every second of every day, more than 6,000 billion neutrinos coming from nuclear reactions inside the sun whiz through my body, almost all of which will travel right through the earth without interruption.', 1129, 0), (471255, 'The poem is not, as someone put it, deflective of entry. But the real question is, ''What happens to the reader once he or she gets inside the poem?'' That''s the real question for me, is getting the reader into the poem and then taking the reader somewhere, because I think of poetry as a kind of form of travel writing.', 8651, 0), (471256, 'I went out to the desert where Cleopatra camped out with her mercenary army. It''s a desolate outpost. Nothing has changed since her day. You realize how far she had to travel. Not only is it a good 150 miles against the current, you can''t take a ship.', 16531, 0), (471257, 'I usually travel with a posse. I roll deep. I travel like a rapper, but without the artillery. We don''t carry guns, we carry cookies.', 69696, 0), (471258, 'Almost all of my jobs have been on locations. And I think you can be that person who says, ''I have a job that forces me to travel and I''m just going to go ahead and do it and pray for my next flight home.'' Or ''this is where I am, this is my life, let me see a part of this world I now live in.''', 38717, 0), (471259, 'In 1967 I entered Harvard as a freshman, confident - in the way that only 17-year-olds are - that I could change the world. My major was African Studies, and my plan was to travel to Tanzania, where President Julius Nyerere was creating a government based on democracy and socialism.', 10602, 0), (471260, 'The Book of Mormon is our handbook of instructions as we travel the pathway from bad to good to better and strive to have our hearts changed.', 11448, 0), (471261, 'The idea of traveling in Africa for me is based on going by road or train or bus or whatever and crossing borders. You can''t travel easily or at all through some countries.', 1979, 0), (471262, 'Antigravity, teleportation, time travel, energetic DNA evolution and consciousness transformation could create a world few of us ever even dreamed of.', 70018, 0), (471263, 'Originally, the burden of proof was on physicists to prove that time travel was possible. Now the burden of proof is on physicists to prove there must be a law forbidding time travel.', 1821, 0), (471264, 'I really cherish the memories I have of my trips. For some reason, when you travel, it''s like your mind picks up on the fact that this is something uncharacteristic, so it tunes in more acutely and remembers better.', 69388, 0), (471265, 'Slow travel now rivals the fly-to-Barcelona-for-lunch culture. Advocates savour the journey, travelling by train or boat or bicycle, or even on foot, rather than crammed into an airplane. They take time to plug into the local culture instead of racing through a list of tourist traps.', 30674, 0), (471266, 'You don''t need to be a spook to care about encryption. If you travel with your computer or keep it in a place where other people can put their hands on it, you''re vulnerable.', 68912, 0), (471267, 'The Patriot Act unleashed the FBI to search your email, travel and credit records without even a suspicion of wrongdoing.', 68912, 0), (471268, 'On stage, you''re not limited at all because you''re free in language: language is the source of the imagination. You can travel farther in language than you can in any film.', 9118, 0), (471269, 'For more and more of us, home has really less to do with a piece of soil than, you could say, with a piece of soul. If somebody suddenly asks me, ''Where''s your home?'' I think about my sweetheart or my closest friends or the songs that travel with me wherever I happen to be.', 711, 0), (471270, 'I want my wife and children to travel always with me and share good things and bad things. That''s what the family is for.', 71362, 0), (471271, 'Making money is often more fun than spending it, though I personally have never regretted money I''ve spent on friends, new experiences, saving time, travel, and causes I believe in.', 68927, 0), (471272, 'A beam of light takes about two million years to reach from us to the Andromeda nebula. But my thought covers this distance in a few seconds. Perhaps some day some intermediate form of body and mind may permit us to say that we actually can travel faster than light.', 74284, 0), (471273, 'My fans are honestly so unique and so similar. Wherever I travel, they are so, so different but so the same.', 68220, 0), (471274, 'The symphonies are the things that, as a soloist, I''ve not gotten to play. I used to travel the world playing concertos, and then I would sit and listen to the symphony.', 67485, 0), (471275, 'I was told at first that being different was a bad thing. Everywhere I went, it was just, ''You''re too different''... And it turned out that being different was the best thing that ever happened to my career. It is why people travel to my shows. It''s why people want to hear my story and buy my book.', 22683, 0), (471276, 'Mom somehow made it to every one of my graduations - even when it meant she had to travel far away.', 68244, 0), (471277, 'The travel book is a convenient metaphor for life, with its optimistic beginning or departure, its determined striving, and its reflective conclusion. Journeys change travellers just as a good travel book can change readers.', 69566, 0), (471278, 'As I travel the world, it seems that younger people identify me merely with some of the folklore in the ''Chuck Norris Facts'' - those hyperbolic sayings that elevate my abilities beyond my capabilities. Others view me in light of the character I played in ''Walker, Texas Ranger'' or in one of my 20 tough-guy films.', 34704, 0), (471279, 'If you think about a lifestyle short of retirement that lends itself to being a hardcore gamer, there is none better than being a major league starting pitcher. I work once every five days and travel and am alone all the time. So while the other guys were spending their money on the all the cars and jewelry, I bought laptops.', 67871, 0), (471280, 'The only way I''m going to support my family is to tour. I love playing, don''t get me wrong. That 90 minutes every night, that''s free. We get paid to travel. But every night, I have to get myself locked in. There are a thousand people that don''t want to be disappointed, because they have a lot of expectations.', 74285, 0), (471281, 'In a great many stories that deal with time travel, there''s usually somebody who knows how time travel works. They lay out the rules.', 74286, 0), (471282, 'In his very first film, Mr. Gonzalez Inarritu makes the kind of journey some directors don''t - or can''t - travel in an entire career.', 68243, 0), (471283, 'Good-quality travel and good-quality food are the two luxuries that I never have any guilt indulging in.', 66790, 0), (471284, 'Background scores allow me an absolute flight of the imagination, and I travel in my mind''s eye. I do not like the scores to have vocal notes, because they act as a limitation to these flights of fancy.', 68260, 0), (471285, 'Just to be a part of something that can travel beyond and reach the lives of people and help them through a daily problem or struggle or even just giving encouraging words, period. I feel like it''s very powerful. I thank God for my gift.', 67890, 0), (471286, 'Fortunately for me, my mother loved travel. Our first non-beach family trip abroad - to England, France, and Switzerland - came when I was 11, and thereafter, we often tagged along on my father''s European business trips.', 572, 0), (471287, 'I have a secret project which adds four hours every day to the 24 hours we have. There''s a bit of time travel involved.', 45284, 0), (471288, 'Restore human legs as a means of travel. Pedestrians rely on food for fuel and need no special parking facilities.', 13474, 0), (471289, 'I like animals. I like natural history. The travel bit is not the important bit. The travel bit is what you have to do in order to go and look at animals.', 3969, 0), (471290, 'It''s wonderful to travel with somebody that you love and we never travel anywhere without one another.', 67012, 0), (471291, 'I want to teach. I want to speak. I want to travel.', 66567, 0), (471292, 'I want to see friends more and travel more.', 883, 0), (471293, 'The thing I love about being an actor is the ability to travel and experience new cultures.', 74287, 0), (471294, 'There are few places you can find silence. Air travel could be the last fortress of solitude.', 37774, 0), (471295, 'The average Londoner knows just one neighbour. I travel a lot, and I''m always surprised by the strong sense of community in some countries. We''ve lost something fundamentally human, and we don''t even realise it.', 74288, 0), (471296, 'I''m a big fan of the laceless Converse for travel, with cute jeans, and throw on a little jacket, and you look presentable.', 69173, 0), (471297, 'I am a control freak, but not when I travel. For some reason when I travel, I am able to surrender more than in my real life. I am able to let go. I think it''s why I like it so much.', 18950, 0), (471298, 'Finney is about the best writer of time travel stories ever, and I adore time travel stories - have to make a time travel game someday!', 69192, 0), (471299, 'I do think that travel can be part of a journey of inner maturation, but you''ve got to do it right.', 639, 0), (471300, 'One of the triumphs of the Civil Rights Movement is that when you travel through the South today, you do not feel overwhelmed by a residue of grievance and hate.', 753, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471301, 'I generally travel with my laptop, a couple of great books, and my iPod.', 68239, 0), (471302, 'There''s going to be space travel at some point.', 68910, 0), (471303, 'When I travel officially... and when I travel on a private basis, I have protection that is less suffocating. But I am protected everywhere.', 67005, 0), (471304, 'I''m generally so disoriented during the week about what I''m doing and where I am - I travel a lot - that when I''m home on a Sunday, I typically try to sleep in as much as I can.', 15814, 0), (471305, 'A travel book is a book that puts you in the shoes of the traveler, and it''s usually a book about having a very bad time; having a miserable time, even better.', 1979, 0), (471306, 'I don''t think I''d be happy if I were satisfied. I enjoy challenge, and I wouldn''t say that I''m an ambitious person career-wise or financially, really. I would like to travel more comfortably, but that''s really about all I need.', 69133, 0), (471307, 'When I had money in the past, I would always travel rather than spend it on big apartments or cars. And I still feel exactly the same way.', 70666, 0), (471308, 'Interviewing Rei Kawakubo in Tokyo and John Galliano in Paris, both for ''Pop'' magazine, were huge for me, not just in learning about fashion and writing but about how little desire I had to be a critic/reporter/journalist/commentator so much as a kind of travel diarist.', 32663, 0), (471309, 'I love to travel, and I think being whisked away somewhere for a vacation is a pretty amazing date. But, I''m really into the basic movie and dinner. It''s not where you are but who you''re with that really matters.', 68435, 0), (471310, 'I do love traveling, so I''ve been able to travel a lot.', 69198, 0), (471311, 'You know you''re a hopeless record nerd when your time travel fantasies always come around to how cool it would be to go back to 1973 and buy all the great funk and jazz and salsa records that came out that year on tiny obscure labels and are now really rare and expensive.', 50328, 0), (471312, 'I just don''t see myself as a travel writer. I can''t. I don''t.', 18322, 0), (471313, 'My keen love of travel was seldom hindered by Father. He permitted me, even as a mere boy, to visit many cities and pilgrimage spots.', 2055, 0), (471314, 'The reason why people wear pajamas to the airport in the first place is so that they''ll be comfortable during their flight. But you know, typically, air travel is 50 to 75 percent of the time you spend traveling. The rest of the time you spend in public places like airports and around other people. That''s when looking good trumps comfort.', 11629, 0), (471315, 'I had rather have a fool to make me merry than experience to make me sad and to travel for it too!', 13, 0), (471316, 'The whole infrastructure of air travel was, and is, part of government policy. It is not a natural development of a free economic system - at least not in the way that is claimed. The same is true of the roads, of course.', 1955, 0), (471317, 'Today, we have private airline companies, but if you take a look at a Boeing plane next time you travel, you''ll see that you are basically taking a ride on a modified bomber.', 1955, 0), (471318, 'I just travel the world with my backpack and my cameras and a bunch of Clif bars.', 68, 0), (471319, 'A lot of Americans don''t have a passport, never will have a passport. Not only will they not travel, they don''t want to travel.', 68, 0), (471320, 'The Bad Seeds are a band I will travel a great distance to see whenever possible.', 68, 0), (471321, 'I do have to travel a lot for speaking engagements.', 10731, 0), (471322, 'I dislike feeling at home when I am abroad.', 266, 0), (471323, 'If you were to actually travel around schools and universities and listen in on lectures about evolution, you might find a fairly substantial fraction of young people, without knowing what it is they disapprove of, think they disapprove of it, because they''ve been brought up to.', 1716, 0), (471324, 'Remember travel agents? Remember how they just kind of vanished one day? Well, that''s where all the other jobs that once made us middle class are going, to that same magical, class-killing, job-sucking wormhole into which travel agency jobs vanished, never to return.', 1002, 0), (471325, 'My favorite books to give or get are short story collections. And always paperbacks because they are easy to carry as you travel.', 30, 0), (471326, 'Fuel prices are at the center of our lives. They affect our ability to travel, stay warm, and feed ourselves.', 66592, 0), (471327, 'Even today, when the Obama administration has liberalized travel to Cuba - and failed to reverse that liberalization when Alan Gross was imprisoned - there are limits.', 67439, 0), (471328, 'When I go back to Texas, I travel the state, and I see people all the time who come up to me, men and women across Texas, and they grab me by the shoulder, and they''re afraid. They say, ''Ted, you know, I just lost my health insurance. I got a child with diabetes. I''m scared. Please stop this from happening.''', 66992, 0), (471329, 'It''s important to travel and move and have a continual set of experiences so you''ve got more to feed back into your work. For me, it''s a natural thing.', 66787, 0), (471330, 'I think the only thing I knew for sure is that I wanted to, whatever I did, I wanted to travel with my work, an adventurous spirit.', 66787, 0), (471331, 'I''ve always said that I use my voice as an instrument. It was something I created myself, and I said, ''Have voice, will travel.''', 1121, 0), (471332, 'I travel a lot, so when I arrive in a city, I like to go to good local bookshops and make a selection based on how I''m feeling and what I''m thinking. The book I pick usually seems to have a definite karmic connection!', 1121, 0), (471333, 'A hybrid human-robot mission to investigate an asteroid affords a realistic opportunity to demonstrate new technological capabilities for future deep-space travel and to test spacecraft for long-duration spaceflight.', 25693, 0), (471334, 'I still make sure to go, at least once every year, to a country where things cannot be taken for granted, and where there is either too much law and order or too little.', 1188, 0), (471335, 'If you are a reader of ''Harper''s Bazaar,'' to me, you are a woman who loves fashion, but not just fashion; you love fashion, you love travel, you love art, you love music.', 67000, 0), (471336, 'The whole object of travel is not to set foot on foreign land it is at last to set foot on one''s own country as a foreign land. ', 67663, 0), (471337, 'I have flown with British Airways since I was a very little child, so it feels quite special to have gone from family holidays flying around Europe to become a gold card holder and be spoiled enough to travel more than not in first class.', 68239, 0), (471338, 'I''m a big fan of doing ''Triple D.'' But I don''t want to do it forever, don''t get me wrong! Travel away from my family, are you crazy? But do you know what it does for these mom-and-pop restaurant joints? It changes their lives forever. I mean, their businesses will never be the same.', 69247, 0), (471339, 'I don''t sleep very well when I travel. And as a result, I tend to be awake in cities when everyone else is asleep.', 67002, 0), (471340, 'It''s hardly a secret that I''m skeptical of declarations that the aliens are out and about on our planet. Still, I try to answer every one of these mails and phone calls because, after all, it''s not a violation of physics to travel from one star system to another.', 13839, 0), (471341, 'While human space travel is daunting, machines - with their indefinitely long lifetimes - could travel the galaxy. It might make little difference to them that bridging the distance from one star to the next could take hundreds of thousands of years or more.', 13839, 0), (471342, 'A practical way to travel between the stars is a must-have for space opera, and a sine qua non for our frequently vaunted future as a galactic society.', 13839, 0), (471343, 'I take a cooking class everywhere I travel. I find it''s the best way to get to know a culture.', 38496, 0), (471344, 'I would love to be a travel writer. I''d be so stoked.', 292, 0), (471345, 'And it was a great experience, you know, to travel the world and compete at a certain level. It teaches you discipline, focus, and certainly keeps you out of trouble.', 68421, 0), (471346, 'I''ve been lucky to travel and work all over the world through the lens of the back of the house, and I love that monocle. I love that lens, because it''s real people.', 32425, 0), (471347, 'It''s often hard for us to imagine going without some of our luxuries like travel, dining out, or Internet, much less our basic necessities like food and water. But try for a minute to imagine how life would be with such deprivations.', 32425, 0), (471348, 'I only travel with a carry-on suitcase in most instances.', 69298, 0), (471349, 'Being an actor, imitating to the point of inhabiting the lives of others, may simply be a way of continuing to do what I learned to do as a boy - to travel, mentally and physically.', 2042, 0), (471350, 'What should I have known or written had I been a quiet, mercantile politician or a lord in waiting? A man must travel, and turmoil, or there is no existence.', 62558, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471351, 'There can be many reasons to travel, but wandering into the world for no particular reason is a sublime madness, which in all its whimsy and pointlessness may depict the story of life - and indeed could be a useful model to keep in mind, seeing as so much of life''s ambition comes unstuck or leads to nothing much at all.', 10407, 0), (471352, 'Science fiction is filled with Martians and space travel to other planets, and things like that.', 114, 0), (471353, 'I love to prune my roses. That''s the one thing I really feel I do pretty well. Other things I usually, because I travel so much, leave to my gardeners who know what I love. But I do love to prune them, because you forget everything else. It''s like if you''re a painter, you can forget everything else while you''re doing it.', 62854, 0), (471354, 'Actually, I had a lot of good people with me - my mother''s sister did a lot of taking care of me, and I suppose I got more attention than my stepbrothers because at least I got to travel with my parents.', 62854, 0), (471355, 'The real luxury travel of the modern age is not through space it''s through time. ', 36805, 0), (471356, 'Our deeds still travel with us from afar, and what we have been makes us what we are.', 215, 0), (471357, 'I collect travel alarm clocks. I was in a flea market in France once, in 1994, and I opened up this beautiful Jaeger-LeCoultre folding eight-day winding clock folded into a beautiful case, and I went, ''Wow, man.'' And I''ve been collecting travel alarm clocks since 1994.', 12582, 0), (471358, 'There are some times when you make films and you travel places, and the take that people in the business have is that the worst way to see a city is to shoot there, because you work these long 12, 13 and 14-hour days, and you go home to the hotel, you eat, and you pass out.', 12582, 0), (471359, 'With the dramatic increase in ease of transportation and the incredible decrease in the amount of time required to travel between far-flung areas of the United States, representatives began spending more and more time in Washington and less and less time in their home districts.', 17797, 0), (471360, 'Schubert had arguably the same melodic gift as Mozart, but even less support. He didn''t have the early exposure, never got to travel anywhere, and yet generated and amassed a body of work that grew and developed and is very profound.', 7842, 0), (471361, 'I dress well. I travel; I seem to be relatively glamorous for a film guy - which, to me, is like being the fastest midget in the circus.', 68243, 0), (471362, 'People in the CIA, they marry each other. They''re like actors! We have to travel without much warning to far-flung places, and it''s very hard to communicate what our experiences are like to those in the outside world.', 70251, 0), (471363, 'I think it''s very important for writers and artists generally to be witnesses to the world, and to be transparent. To let other people speak... to travel... to experience the world. And memorialize it.', 852, 0), (471364, 'Through machinery, man can exert tremendous powers almost as fantastic as if he were the hero of a fairy tale. Through machinery, man can travel with an ever increasing velocity; he can fly through the air and go beneath the surface of the ocean.', 11408, 0), (471365, 'I do not like people touching my underwear. That''s just weird! I travel with a washer and dryer, and I like cooking on the bus, too.', 452, 0), (471366, 'The glamour of air travel - its aspirational meaning in the public imagination - disappeared before its luxury did, dissipating as flying gradually became commonplace.', 68175, 0), (471367, 'The glamour of twentieth-century air travel helped to persuade once-fearful travelers to take to the skies and encouraged parochial Americans to go out and see the world.', 68175, 0), (471368, 'People without children do have the freedom to do things that caring parents with dependent kids can''t - to work long hours, to travel frequently, to relocate, and to do all these things on short notice if necessary. In return, they can achieve positions that devoted parents can''t.', 68175, 0), (471369, 'I just can''t do heels any more. At least not when I''m working. I travel a lot.', 67831, 0), (471370, 'Under the cover of encryption, terror masterminds provide recruits with the tactics and tools necessary to carry out attacks using small arms and explosives. None of this requires any overseas travel.', 67008, 0), (471371, 'Today, few terrorist organizations still employ the ''al-Qaeda model'' in which individuals travel to terrorist training camps overseas and then are deployed to the West to inflict atrocities.', 67008, 0), (471372, 'The first time probably people really were aware of me, I unfortunately had the title of Showtime''s Funniest Person in America. And that''s a really tough title to travel around with when you''re not even known.', 1217, 0), (471373, 'If I were involved with the NBA, I wouldn''t want a 19-year-old or a 20-year-old kid to bring into all the travel and all the problems that exist in the NBA. I would want a much more mature kid. I would want a kid that maybe I''ve been watching on another team, and now he''s 21, 22 years old instead of 18 or 19, and I might trade for that kid.', 7610, 0), (471374, 'I read on my iPad when I travel. I listen to audiobooks in the car. I read books in my bedroom, where I have a comfortable couch, a lamp and two dogs to keep me warm.', 441, 0), (471375, 'I collect a lot of clothes when I travel around the world.', 67009, 0), (471376, 'A wise traveler never despises his own country.', 8948, 0), (471377, 'It is not fit that every man should travel; it makes a wise man better, and a fool worse.', 8948, 0), (471378, 'As a Global Maternal Health Advocate, I get to travel the world quite a bit, meeting individuals and visiting programs with tremendous potential and incredible vision to improve the quality of life for countless others.', 69119, 0), (471379, 'People forget I go to work. They forget that the Coleridge house was bought and paid for by the daughter of a travel agent and a barmaid from what the actor Richard Burton once described as the nightmarish ''featureless suburb'' of Croydon.', 12807, 0), (471380, 'It was a rural upbringing by the seaside. A real quiet place surrounded by fields. I had to travel into town for school and stuff like that.', 70665, 0), (471381, 'I travel all the time, but when I come back to the South, I see such progress. In a real sense, a great deal of the South has been redeemed. People feel freer, more complete, more whole, because of what happened in the movement.', 36727, 0), (471382, 'Technology doesn''t address everything - for example, air travel still sucks.', 66612, 0), (471383, 'You define a good flight by negatives: you didn''t get hijacked, you didn''t crash, you didn''t throw up, you weren''t late, you weren''t nauseated by the food. So you are grateful.', 1979, 0), (471384, 'I think people read travel books either because they intend to take that trip, or because they would never take that trip. In a sense, as a writer you are doing the travel for the reader.', 1979, 0), (471385, 'One of the things the ''Tao of Travel'' shows is how unforthcoming most travel writers are, how most travelers are. They don''t tell you who they were traveling with, and they''re not very reliable about things that happened to them.', 1979, 0), (471386, 'The job of the travel writer is to go far and wide, to make voluminous notes, to tell the truth.', 1979, 0), (471387, 'Extensive traveling induces a feeling of encapsulation, and travel, so broadening at first, contracts the mind.', 1979, 0), (471388, 'A travel book is about someone who goes somewhere, travels on the ground, sees something and spends quite a lot of time doing it, and has a hard time, and then comes back and writes about it. It''s not about inventing.', 1979, 0), (471389, 'Mark Twain was a great traveler and he wrote three or four great travel books. I wouldn''t say that I''m a travel novelist but rather a novelist who travels - and who uses travel as a background for finding stories of places.', 1979, 0), (471390, 'I was raised in a large family. The first reason for my travel was to get away from my family. I knew that I wanted to be a writer, but I didn''t want people to ask me questions about it.', 1979, 0), (471391, 'The worst thing that can happen to you in travel is having a gun pointed at you by a very young person. That''s happened to me maybe four times in my life. I didn''t like it.', 1979, 0), (471392, 'The appeal of travel books is also the sense that you are different, an outsider, almost like the Robinson Crusoe or Christopher Columbus notion of being the first person in a new place.', 1979, 0), (471393, 'I wouldn''t say that I''m a travel novelist, but rather a novelist who travels - and who uses travel as a background for finding stories of places.', 1979, 0), (471394, 'The travel impulse is mental and physical curiosity. It''s a passion. And I can''t understand people who don''t want to travel.', 1979, 0), (471395, 'There is simply no defending the preferred mode of travel for many of the celebrity crazies who lecture us about carbon credits. Do you think these folks are willing to give up their mansions and private jets in order to ''save the planet?''', 68915, 0), (471396, 'I think it''s important that kids have responsibilities and understand the value of things, but I think it''s great I get to travel the world with my daughter.', 68376, 0), (471397, 'I''m a little bit phobic about stains on my clothes, so I never travel without a little packet of organic stain remover.', 18212, 0), (471398, 'I like to go to work, and also, I don''t have any kids. I don''t have any hobbies. I don''t like to travel. So going to work is kind of it.', 67388, 0), (471399, 'My life is really quite conservative. I''ve been married nearly 50 years. I don''t have hobbies or children. I don''t much care to travel. I''ve never had a big social life. I really just stay home, except when I go to work.', 67388, 0), (471400, 'I always want off-the-beaten-path, Anthony Bourdain-inspired travel.', 69330, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471401, 'On a normal day, I love a shift dress with flats and a little cropped jacket. That, for me, is my travel wear if it''s not too chilly - you can throw a scarf over your legs if it''s cold on the plane!', 69330, 0), (471402, 'Utrip makes it easy for travelers to experience the destination highlights that most interest them, be it food, art or history. Just like a culinary experience, every palate is different, and Utrip is all about personalizing travel for their users.', 72052, 0), (471403, 'I have two kids, career and I travel, and I don''t think my life is any different than most couples. The most valuable commodity now for many people is time and how to parcel that out.', 43985, 0), (471404, 'I like to engage the public because when I was in high school, I had all these questions about anti-matter, higher dimensions and time travel. Every time I went to the library, every time I asked people these questions, I would get some strange looks. Nobody could answer any of these questions.', 1821, 0), (471405, 'Time travel and teleportation will have to wait. It may take centuries to master these technology. But within the coming decades, we will understand dark matter, perhaps test string theory, find planets which can harbor life, and maybe have Brain 2.0, i.e. our consciousness on a disk which will survive even after we die.', 1821, 0), (471406, 'When you grow up in a place, you always think it''s mundane. Then you travel around and live in different places, and you realise that you''ve got it the wrong way ''round.', 1425, 0), (471407, 'It''s very expensive to be a professional tennis player with all the travel and the flights and the hotels and everything.', 69728, 0), (471408, 'Social media has allowed groups, such as ISIL, to use the Internet to spot and assess potential recruits. With the widespread horizontal distribution of social media, terrorists can identify vulnerable individuals of all ages in the United States - spot, assess, recruit, and radicalize - either to travel or to conduct a homeland attack.', 67558, 0), (471409, 'People just hate the idea of losing. Any loss, even a small one, is just so terrible to contemplate that they compensate by buying insurance, including totally absurd policies like air travel.', 6017, 0), (471410, 'I think kids ought to travel. I think it''s very good to carry kids around. It''s good for them. Of course it''s tough on the parents.', 217, 0), (471411, 'At some point, the government expands into the private sphere so far that you live in a place with a whole lot less freedom. I didn''t like that that was the direction of travel for our country, and decided to come to Washington to try and be a small part of bringing it back.', 68917, 0), (471412, 'Travel makes a wise man better, and a fool worse.', 1348, 0), (471413, 'Strange - is it not? That of the myriads who Before us passed the door of Darkness through, Not one returns to tell us of the road Which to discover we must travel too.', 2542, 0), (471414, 'I mean, I''d love to have a private jet - I know people who fly by private jet all the time... I''ve hitched a ride a few times and it is not overrated at all; it''s a great way to travel!', 19768, 0), (471415, 'Now, I have a kid, I have businesses to take care of, I have to travel. I have to sit down... and find a little time for me.', 14526, 0), (471416, 'My favorite spot is the Maldives. Since I travel so much for work, I like to go to places that are very secluded and quiet.', 67736, 0), (471417, 'I don''t buy a lot when I travel, but when I do, I like to send gifts from wherever I am. It''s fun to find the local post office.', 67016, 0), (471418, 'One of the things that I love to do is travel around the world and look at archaeological sites. Because archaeology gives us an opportunity to study past civilizations, and see where they succeeded and where they failed. Use science to, you know, work backwards and say, ''Well, really, what were they thinking?''', 10715, 0), (471419, 'The way Moore''s Law occurs in computing is really unprecedented in other walks of life. If the Boeing 747 obeyed Moore''s Law, it would travel a million miles an hour, it would be shrunken down in size, and a trip to New York would cost about five dollars. Those enormous changes just aren''t part of our everyday experience.', 10715, 0), (471420, 'Very early on, when I started doing these plays and live shows, I would travel from city to city, and there were a million shows out there... so I wanted to step out among it, and I started putting my name above the title.', 1776, 0), (471421, 'Sometimes you want to go for a walk and you don''t want to be watched. You just want to be anonymous and blend in. Especially when I travel, I feel that way, because I can''t really go out and see a city the way other people can and I miss out on a lot.', 67561, 0), (471422, 'Work done by other people sounds easy. How hard can it be to take care of a newborn who sleeps 20 hours a day? How hard can it be to keep track of your billable hours? To travel for one night for business? To get a 4-year-old ready for school? To return a few phone calls? To load the dishwasher? To fill out some forms?', 3243, 0), (471423, 'When ''Apollo 13'' appeared as an opportunity and I began to tackle that in as authentic a way as I possibly could, I really became enthralled by the philosophical side of space travel and why we need to explore - what it means to us here on Earth - all of those things. I became a huge proponent.', 69923, 0), (471424, 'After a lifetime of world travel I''ve been fascinated that those in the third world don''t have the same perception of reality that we do.', 2687, 0), (471425, 'Age focuses you. You are much better concentrated. There''s more time when you travel less, don''t do book tours, avoid interviews or public appearances. You walk the dogs, fish, hunt, cook and write.', 2687, 0), (471426, 'I travel with Club Glove.', 66923, 0), (471427, 'My son is so fortunate, you know. He''s always going to have food. Yes, my children are going to be privileged, but that''s why it''s so important for them to see different realities and to travel, and they do already.', 47135, 0), (471428, 'I live in a town called Beerwah, right in the middle of Australia Zoo. It''s not hustle and bustle and busy, so that''s helpful. We travel all over the world, but I''ve always been able to come home and run around in the middle of the Australian outback.', 68250, 0), (471429, 'I guess, growing up at Australia Zoo and getting to travel all over the world, I have this great outlook on life, and that''s what I hope I inspire other kids to have.', 68250, 0), (471430, 'My family didn''t have money to travel, so reading was how I knew about the world. It made me hungry to have more experiences than just what I could possibly experience in Arkansas.', 70220, 0), (471431, 'Any time I have any time off, I try to travel.', 68181, 0), (471432, 'My jet lag is getting a bit ridiculous. But, you know, it''s first-world problems. It''s a wonderful problem, ''Oh I have to travel around the world; how awful.''', 68181, 0), (471433, 'We have so much pride in welcoming these passengers onto the plane, and they have so much pride in travel. It''s something that I definitely always remember, when I''m playing a scene on the plane, just to imbue everything with that sense of excitement.', 69337, 0), (471434, 'When I''m in London I do have the convenience of being close to St James Park which is also good for me because it gives me an excuse to get out and get some much needed exercise!', 67458, 0), (471435, 'The more I travel around the world, the more I see people want the same thing - to be happy. We wouldn''t be in a monetary system if we didn''t have to work, so if my music can contribute to happiness, then that''s my main responsibility.', 397, 0), (471436, 'I only travel with one suitcase - Mulberry does an incredible one. I always check it the TSA restrictions are so tricky. ', 69238, 0), (471437, 'I like to stay home with my family. But travel is good in a way. It makes you redefine each other each time you see each other. Also, it helps that I think my wife is the hottest woman in the world.', 69339, 0), (471438, 'If I could travel back in time, I''d bring back the entire Wu-Tang Clan.', 69341, 0), (471439, 'I wouldn''t call it a faux pas, but I have about 12 tracksuits. I always travel in a tracksuit. I feel it makes people happy when they see me.', 67397, 0), (471440, 'I do kabbalistic meditation. It''s not unlike time travel it can change the past and not just the future. You can look at what was lost and go beyond the grief of what was lost. ', 18054, 0), (471441, 'Travel is hard, but entertaining is joy.', 43585, 0), (471442, 'Terror, married to technology and accommodated by progress in travel, has turned evil individuals into traveling ballistic missiles.', 10679, 0), (471443, 'There was a film that really affected me, ''La Strada'' by Fellini, where Anthony Quinn and Giulietta Masina travel around on his little motorcycle thing.', 4792, 0), (471444, 'Along with that ongoing process Sinn Fein took a decision to establish a peace commission which had the responsibility to travel around the country to receive submissions from the general public, also our opponents.', 67683, 0), (471445, 'I was lucky enough to have it all. To be successful in business, to have children, to raise them on my own, and to travel and live my life. It was a lot of work, but it''s a privilege to have been able to do it.', 1088, 0), (471446, 'My pals, such as they are, in Hollywood, ask me why I love to travel to D.C. so much, why it''s a vacation destination for me. I say, ''Because I sometimes have perfect days there.''', 34057, 0), (471447, 'Space doesn''t offer an escape from Earth''s problems. And even with nuclear fuel, the transit time to nearby stars exceeds a human lifetime. Interstellar travel is therefore, in my view, an enterprise for post-humans, evolved from our species not via natural selection, but by design.', 67022, 0), (471448, 'The first voyagers to the stars will be creatures whose life cycle is matched to the voyage: the aeons involved in traversing the galaxy are not daunting to immortal beings. By the end of the third millennium, travel to other stars could be technically feasible. But would there be sufficient motive?', 67022, 0), (471449, 'With all the travel we''re doing to cold-weather cities, your mind definitely starts to wander. It gets you away from the game. Even when you arrive in a city, you''re tempted to just sit in your hotel and rest. Sometimes it''s nice to just get out and walk around, to see what''s there.', 69121, 0), (471450, 'I hope to play until I''m, like, 38 or something, and that''s a lot of years in the game and a lot of travel and a lot of sacrifice on my family''s part.', 69121, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471451, 'When you travel so many weeks a year, it''s always nice to have a home-cooked meal.', 68355, 0), (471452, 'When I travel, I love speaking to women around the world about the things that inspire them, the fashions they like, what makes something good and what would make it even better.', 68355, 0), (471453, 'I''ve been fortunate enough to travel the world because of my career, but the downside has been spending long spells apart from my daughters.', 68437, 0), (471454, 'I''ve three children, three grandchildren, I work, I travel, and I''m very happily married. I''m very satisfied and happy with my life and there really isn''t anything I want.', 50885, 0), (471455, 'I think a major element of jetlag is psychological. Nobody ever tells me what time it is at home.', 3969, 0), (471456, 'Building and launching rockets has been a lifelong hobby that my son and I share. We regularly travel to Nevada''s Black Rock Desert to launch rockets.', 68924, 0), (471457, 'But as far as being an American and loving this country and getting a chance to travel across it every day and meeting people on the road and folks in the military, I love this country on so many different levels.', 69345, 0), (471458, 'With Pakistan being in my blood, I would certainly look at opportunities to travel there.', 68008, 0), (471459, 'I was tall and skinny, and at 15, I was approached to model. I figured that models got to travel, and it became my ticket to travel so much so that if an agency could not fly me to another country, I would fly on my cost so that I could see that country and also make some money.', 68008, 0), (471460, 'Thanks to having my dad travel with me, I don''t feel quite cut off from my family.', 69348, 0), (471461, 'I do not own a car, and my main form of travel to Westminster and in my constituency is by bicycle. I also take my bike on trains to meetings in other parts of the country, which enables me to see other cities and the other parts of the country.', 50602, 0), (471462, 'You can tell all our songs come from us and from our artists, the people we write with and travel with.', 69085, 0), (471463, 'At my age, I only travel business class because I just don''t bend anymore; my body can''t cope with it.', 19787, 0), (471464, 'I try to ensure my daughters are not spoilt. They are very aware of how lucky they are and appreciate it. We have had some lean years, so they know it''s not all about luxury, travel, and hotels. They are grounded, and I''m grateful for that.', 70638, 0), (471465, 'For years, I meant to read ''Arabian Sands'', Wilfred Thesiger''s account of two punishing camel journeys during the late 1940s across Southern Arabia''s Empty Quarter. Now that I have, I can sheepishly join the chorus of those who revere the book as one of the half dozen greatest works of modern English travel writing.', 14168, 0), (471466, 'Snowboarding''s tough, because you''ve got to go to the mountains. For me, I love the skateboard season because I get to hangout at home and still be skating. I don''t have to travel to Norway or Japan or these crazy places to be snowboarding.', 67034, 0), (471467, 'No veteran or active duty service member should endure a long hospital stay alone. Yet sadly, due to the high cost of travel, all too often our military families are separated while America''s heroes receive care. Sometimes families sleep in hospital parking lots, unable to afford long stays in a hotel.', 71180, 0), (471468, 'I love to travel. This is the time for me. When will I do it if not now?', 68929, 0), (471469, 'I took a gap year myself after high school and worked on a farm near Lyon, France. I stayed with the Vallet family, picked and packed fruit, and discovered that red wine can be a breakfast drink. That led to further travel as a university student.', 47722, 0), (471470, 'I travel all the time. And as I go around the world, I try to learn a little something and not just take up all the available air.', 67834, 0), (471471, 'We travel a lot and don''t get enough time to spend with our family, and so we have to take our pictures, videos, also bother about things like which are the HD quality phones. So I''m very much a part of these typical things.', 67036, 0), (471472, 'After you pay your E-ZPass bill, there is no reason for the government to keep records of your travel.', 73568, 0), (471473, 'It''s sometimes tiring to get off a long-haul flight and go straight to the studio for a shoot, but if you really plan everything well, you can get so much out of combining travel with work.', 68265, 0), (471474, 'The beauty of reading is that it lets you travel in a way you could never know.', 68265, 0), (471475, 'I got to travel around Anbar Province, had a great group of Marines who worked for me who traveled around Anbar Province. I got to hang out with a lot of different types of Marines and soldiers and sailors.', 30972, 0), (471476, 'I really enjoy what I do, and who I''m with and where I am. Having said that, I''m not really a person of habit, because what I do in my job is travel around the world and play concerts to people, and occasionally do very weird things.', 68214, 0), (471477, 'No one working as an astronomer is shackled in chains. This is a tremendous profession. There are lots of neat people, and you get to do cool things. If I had to say something negative, it''s that there''s often a whole lot of travel that takes me away from my children. That can be a bummer a lot of times.', 66716, 0), (471478, 'I have no idea what it would be like to be just one thing and speak one language. I feel enormously privileged to travel and be able to mingle and speak to people that, had I only known English, I wouldn''t have been able to meet.', 70058, 0), (471479, 'I lost all my investments after everything crashed in 2001. Prior to that, I''d been living off the interest on my investments, which was very healthy because it allowed frequent travel, and I had a lovely apartment.', 72054, 0), (471480, 'If I''m on holiday, I travel light, but if it is a work trip, I take everything but the kitchen sink.', 72054, 0), (471481, 'I literally wear a mask. When I take it off, I''m a father. I''m a husband. I like to come home, and I like to spend time with family, and I like to travel, and I like to have a good time. And I like to be a kid every now and giggle and play with my kids.', 67038, 0), (471482, 'I run five miles three times a week I log everything. I look up routes when I travel. ', 67039, 0), (471483, 'I just see too many people retire and say, ''I''m going to take off, travel, spend time with my family'' and they are just miserable. They end up dying. People who work and stay active, and like what they are doing, live longer.', 67040, 0), (471484, 'To build my legacy and be that person I want to be, this is what it''s going to take: to get on the road and travel. Let''s do it that way.', 71235, 0), (471485, 'The future continues to preoccupy me as a reliable source of hopes, fears and anxieties, but increasingly the present seems to have no outstanding qualities of its own, being merely a way-station through which events travel to the vast shadow lands of the past.', 1747, 0), (471486, 'The first book I did - the first successful book - was a kind of a travel book, and publishers in Britain encouraged me to do more.', 1068, 0), (471487, 'I understand more when I travel why people believe that the French are arrogant.', 66933, 0), (471488, 'Startups, in some sense, have gotten so easy to start that we are confusing two things. And what we are confusing, often, is, ''How far can you get in your first day of travel?'' with, ''How long it is going to take to get up to the top of the mountain?''', 66968, 0), (471489, 'News seems to travel far more quickly on Twitter and Facebook than through search.', 70059, 0), (471490, 'Data can generally travel the speed of light unless networks are congested. When there''s congestion, usually the cheapest and best thing is simply to add capacity generally, not to prioritize certain sites over others.', 70059, 0), (471491, 'Yes, I travel in unusual circles. George Osborne and his wife Frances are my cousins.', 68394, 0), (471492, 'Among the various vernaculars that are spoken in different parts of India, there is one that stands out strongly from the rest, as that which is most widely known. It is Hindi. A man who knows Hindi can travel over India and find everywhere Hindi-speaking people.', 4208, 0), (471493, 'When I thought I was retired, I wanted to travel around the world and watch soccer games.', 1184, 0), (471494, 'In general, when you travel, you get into a different reality and are able to more accurately reflect on your ordinary life. Hiking does that for me.', 66656, 0), (471495, 'I love my cooking tools because I enjoy cooking - a Vitamix for smoothies and a rice cooker for steel-cut oats. I travel with a small rice cooker. I soak oats overnight, and when I get up, I just turn the rice cooker on, and it cooks the oats perfectly every time.', 66656, 0), (471496, 'Air travel is the safest form of travel aside from walking; even then, the chances of being hit by a public bus at 30,000 feet are remarkably slim. I also have no problem with confined spaces. Or heights. What I am afraid of is speed.', 1436, 0), (471497, 'People who might normally have to travel hours to a distant city to see a cardiologist can now do so virtually, through Cisco technology, at their local hospital or health clinic. Clinicians use technology to share patient reports and diagnostic images and collaborate on cases.', 70948, 0), (471498, 'I have been lucky enough to travel a lot, meet great people in many lands. I have liked almost everyone I met along the way.', 556, 0), (471499, 'Ball caps travel far and wide. They do far more than keep the sun out of your eyes or the cold off your head. Ball caps are a statement.', 67719, 0), (471500, 'No matter where I travel in the state, people want to talk about education.', 66642, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471501, 'Don''t get me wrong, I love watching episodes of my favorite shows on Hulu and reading the daily trash on PageSix, but I also embrace the opportunity to settle down with a good book and let my mind travel to another place and time.', 69076, 0), (471502, 'We are ramping up security in the United States but also looking at visa applicants, visa waiver applicants - and looking at travel manifests on the airplanes trying to come into the United States.', 68931, 0), (471503, 'It''s one thing for someone to travel over to Syria and Iraq and come back. But, boy, it''s a lot easier if they activate someone who''s already here.', 68931, 0), (471504, 'On Sundays, we would travel to the town and watch English movies. This way, we must have ended up watching some 1,000 movies during college.', 67050, 0), (471505, 'Of all possible subjects, travel is the most difficult for an artist, as it is the easiest for a journalist.', 219, 0), (471506, 'It doesn''t require much thought for one to realise that any travel book worthy of the name has to be a departure from the standard idea of the form.', 9638, 0), (471507, 'I considered becoming a priest very seriously. I wanted to travel the world. By the time I turned 16, I realized I was only in it for selfish reasons. And, more importantly, I didn''t want to sacrifice the ladies!', 70221, 0), (471508, 'I actually think some of my best moments in life have been while I was with people from Instagram - whether it''s super late nights getting a release out or being able to travel to places I''d never visited and meeting some of the most interesting people I''ve ever met.', 69503, 0), (471509, 'I coach soccer, and my wife and I are very involved in our kids'' lives. Our family is busy with doctor appointments, soccer practice, school, work, travel, vacation... life.', 17487, 0), (471510, 'From a pretty early age, my mother realized that I was a little bit more gifted and talented than my own age group. So, she moved me over to play with the boys'' travel soccer team when I was about 11 years old.', 67372, 0), (471511, 'All this misjudgment that we have of each other is based on ignorance. The second you get to travel, you see that human beings, no matter where they come from, they are the same.', 2030, 0), (471512, 'We link our future to the euro, to the euro zone, and to the European Union while being the nearest neighbor of the United Kingdom with, obviously, a common travel area and a very close working relationship with the U.K.', 68933, 0), (471513, 'I had to travel into the future and direct ''Jurassic World'' as myself in 20 years - and I did.', 74266, 0), (471514, 'And now I have a big house, nice clothes and I travel in first class and I love it, so maybe it''s time to enjoy being a star.', 74289, 0), (471515, 'I really encourage people to travel so we can see how the rest of the world views our country. That''s really important. Secondly, as artists, activists, and citizens who vote, we have to begin to vote from our heart.', 21674, 0), (471516, 'The world is a country which nobody ever yet knew by description one must travel through it one''s self to be acquainted with it. ', 68382, 0), (471517, 'I''ve thought it would be cool to have a baby young. You know, be my road dog - like my dogs, they travel the world - but there''s always something you have to give up for success. Everything comes at a cost. Just what are you willing to pay for it?', 70497, 0), (471518, 'I have a couple of go-to sneakers off the pitch. I like to have shoes that I can slip on and wear with anything. I travel often, so it''s about finding those two or three pairs of shoes that can go with any outfit, whether they go with leggings or a skirt or a dress or jeans.', 67841, 0), (471519, 'For a long time, our only mode of travel was an Econoline van. Eleven of us, with nine sleeping in the back on two mattresses.', 71036, 0), (471520, 'Oh, I''m terrible at travel.', 67052, 0), (471521, 'Travel for me is all about transformation, and I''m fascinated by those people who really do come back from a trip unrecognizable to themselves and perhaps open to the same possibilities they''d have written off not a month before.', 711, 0), (471522, 'I think writing is really about a journey of understanding. So you take something that seems very far away, and the more you write about it, the more you travel into it, and you see it from within.', 711, 0), (471523, 'I think one reason, obviously, that I spend so much time in one place is that I''ve been lucky enough to travel a lot, and now there are other different, invisible trains that are more interesting to me.', 711, 0), (471524, 'We all know how we can be turned around by a magic place; that''s why we travel, often. And yet we all know, too, that the change cannot be guaranteed. Travel is a fool''s paradise, Emerson reminded us, if we think that we can find anything far off that we could not find at home.', 711, 0), (471525, 'Being in a band is like a small family. You travel together, make music, and share time with each other.', 67868, 0), (471526, 'Young people should travel, and they don''t. You can''t know if you don''t go.', 28763, 0), (471527, 'I travel like a maniac. I travel more than anyone I know. I love learning the languages.', 28763, 0), (471528, 'I lived in Italy for two months when I was in college. And I traveled to Paris. I traveled to Egypt. I traveled to Spain. I just would travel a lot. I remember going to Paris and saying, speaking French, ''I would like some chicken and some fries.'' And just the chicken and fries was, oh my gosh, just so amazing. I became intrigued and inspired.', 68272, 0), (471529, 'I''ve been all over the world on my own because, as a scientist, you travel a great deal if your work is reasonably successful or published. I get invitations to go to all sorts of strange countries where I would mostly be by myself and just meet other people there, instead of having travelling companions.', 69138, 0), (471530, 'America has the best hand ever dealt to any country on this planet, ever. Yes, we have problems, but you travel around the world, you''ll see we have it all.', 66585, 0), (471531, 'I started to travel like this at the age of 15 so for me, it''s normal. Some days you get tired and you feel, ''I want to stay at home a little bit more,'' but it''s only the moment.', 27470, 0), (471532, 'There is no budget for travel for a Shadow Foreign Secretary.', 70519, 0), (471533, 'The Internet is part of our evolution. The mystics used to say, ''We can travel across the planet in a thought.'' Now we really can. We can be connected with a million people at a time.', 37699, 0), (471534, 'I think every day how incredibly lucky it is that I travel around the world playing to thousands of people.', 30112, 0), (471535, 'Tyga''s one of my best friends ever, so it''s so much fun to travel with him. I always like having my friends out on the road with me.', 66658, 0), (471536, 'I want to go to college to study journalism. I want to speak French fluently, to travel. My mom was a journalist and it''s in my blood.', 67484, 0), (471537, 'Interesting things come your way but as you get older, your lifestyle changes. I don''t want to travel; I don''t want to be in a hotel room away from my family.', 3625, 0), (471538, 'There are so many things I want to do. Like, I want to get an artist, a musician, a photographer, and a bunch of dancers that I know and just travel across Africa and just film it and just see what happens. Do and learn as much as I possibly can. Luckily, I have a lot more time.', 68275, 0), (471539, 'I travel a lot and rarely make it home to Seattle.', 29415, 0), (471540, 'I wish more Americans would travel here. I always encourage my friends: ''Travel. See the Middle East. There''s so much to see, so many good people.'' And it''s vice versa, and it helps stop problems of misunderstanding and stereotypes from happening.', 50659, 0), (471541, 'Anyone who''s gotten their passport in America will tell you, when you get it, it still says what country you were born in. So I remember getting my American passport. I was like, ''Woo-hoo! I''m going to travel.'' And I opened it up. It said, ''Born in Iran.'' I''m like, ''Oh, come on, man!''', 50659, 0), (471542, 'My family went to Toronto to visit relatives when I was 13 or 14. It was the first time we had ever been abroad. This was the early Eighties, and I remember the impossible glamour of air travel - my mum spending days trying to decide what she was going to wear on the plane.', 27413, 0), (471543, 'I get cold - really cold - when I travel.', 10905, 0), (471544, 'Look how far the human race has come in terms of air and space travel in the last hundred years. So in the next couple of thousand years, you''ve got to believe that we''re going to be able to do all kinds of amazing things.', 73999, 0), (471545, 'I try and work out as often as possible. Since I travel very often, it becomes very difficult to have a daily work out routine, but I practice yoga every day or try and play some sport. Also, I am very aware of what suits my body in terms of food and exercise.', 69743, 0), (471546, 'I''ve always believed that as actors, one of the biggest advantages of being in the film business - not just of being actors, but being in this industry - is the fact that you get to travel so much, and you get to see places that you probably would not if you went just as a tourist.', 69743, 0), (471547, 'I don''t like hobbies. I read and travel and see my friends before they disown me.', 70675, 0), (471548, 'Furloughing a bunch of air traffic controllers has a pretty easy-to-predict effect on air travel: It causes delays.', 68448, 0), (471549, 'I like to watch Bourdain and Andrew Zimmern, because I like them when they travel. I like Ina Garten, ''The Barefoot Contessa.'' Giada is really nice, but I get a little bit bored with just staying in the kitchen.', 66987, 0), (471550, 'I was a huge Beatles fan. We could talk about who I listened to growing up and what my sources were, but certainly the Beatles were a late, important resource for me, and I just took my guitar and a handful of songs, and I decided, well, I''ll just go over and travel around Europe and see what comes of it.', 68940, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471551, 'The myth-making about Appomattox started from the moment Lee left the courthouse on his horse to travel to Richmond.', 19715, 0), (471552, 'I do this system called TRX. It was developed by a Navy SEAL and is basically a simple cord that you can wrap around something anywhere, anytime, and you use your body weight as resistance. We installed one in our home gym, but you can also attach it to a tree. It''s very easy to travel with.', 68450, 0), (471553, 'My job is to be a spokesman - the spokesman, I suppose - for the President, for the White House, to do the daily briefings, to manage the press corps in terms of travel, day-to-day needs, access, interviews, all those issues.', 68451, 0), (471554, 'Americans aren''t good at accents, but the English are because their accents change. You go five or six blocks and the accent is different, so they are used to hearing different pitches. In America, you gotta travel maybe 10 states before you can really hear a difference.', 68943, 0), (471555, 'I''ve gotten very cynical and kind of anhedonic about all the things I have to do to get to do comedy: all the travel, hotels, and airports.', 6537, 0), (471556, 'I travel all over the world, usually 10 months out of the year. I stay at a lot of hotels, and the ones I like best are clean and not complicated. You go to bed and say, ''Wow, I feel comfortable.''', 71309, 0), (471557, 'When I travel too much, it affects the music, and that is the most important thing. As long as I make good music, I can play shows, but if the music starts getting bad, the show offers won''t come.', 69357, 0), (471558, 'In between films I like to travel and hope to visit every continent before I become a mother.', 70263, 0), (471559, '''Naked'' kind of kicked me off into the film world. It just so happens that all of the things that I have been offered have been films, and I''ve enjoyed the travel that goes along with that.', 5946, 0), (471560, 'I fly economy. I do often fly first class, but I don''t travel with a posse, or bodyguard, or an assistant.', 11192, 0), (471561, 'I am humbled and excited by new opportunities for me to support and share the amazing work NASA is doing to help us travel farther into the solar system and work with the next generation of science and technology leaders.', 51306, 0), (471562, 'There are few aspects of everyday life that aren''t touched by the technologies developed for space travel.', 51306, 0), (471563, 'I''m such a girl for the living room. I really like to stay in my nest and not move. I travel in my mind, and that that''s a rigorous state of journeying for me. My body isn''t that interested in moving from place to place.', 218, 0), (471564, 'Beauty, pleasure, freedom and plenty of sleep: these are the hallmarks of a successful idler''s break. Travel should not be hard work.', 16461, 0), (471565, 'I love to take risks, I love to travel, and I''m very outdoor-sy, so any girl who can pick up a football and throw a spiral will definitely catch my attention.', 53743, 0), (471566, 'As far as ''Twilight'' goes, I''m in love with my character. I''m in love with the whole series. I love doing the fan conventions around the world, I love to travel. So wherever it fits in, I''d love to continue doing that for the rest of my life. Just meeting the fans who made everything possible from around the world.', 53743, 0), (471567, 'Everywhere I travel around my home state of Wyoming - but also around the country - I continue to hear, ''How can Washington make us buy something we don''t want to buy, a product? They can''t tell us to buy breakfast cereal or something else - how can they do that?''', 73044, 0), (471568, 'I travel the world, and I can see in Toronto the cooking is very personal. These people cook with their hearts.', 67872, 0), (471569, 'If I had the choice to travel to two places in Europe, it would be Paris and London.', 67872, 0), (471570, 'Given the number of restaurants I have, I could easily travel all the time - but I try not to.', 67872, 0), (471571, 'I loved working on ''Happy Gilmore'' because I love to travel to new places and we got to go to British Columbia. Any Adam Sandler film is fun to work on because it is a reunion of the boys club of guys that have worked together in the past.', 69746, 0), (471572, 'I never get enough sleep, even when I travel. I wake up in the middle of the night, either with the help of my kids or because my mind is going. I wish I got eight hours a night, but it is more like an interrupted six or seven. The secret is to go to sleep well before midnight.', 67751, 0), (471573, 'I love to run, but training can be hard, especially with a family and a crazy travel schedule. I often do sprints with my kids, where they bike and I run along side them so we can ''race'' each other for a quarter-mile or shorter repeats.', 67751, 0), (471574, 'I love to not work. I like to travel. I work maybe half the year, no more.', 3217, 0), (471575, 'Unfortunately, I''m more experienced than I care to admit on long-distance relationships. Just because that is my life. I travel because I love to. As a result, I have to sort of make it work when a relationship kind of comes into view.', 48278, 0), (471576, 'Modeling isn''t really a tough job. Acting is much harder: so much prep and changing your look and mannerisms. It''s a more difficult lifestyle being a model. I traveled all the time. Although, now I wonder, because I travel all the time for acting, too. So they both have their difficulties.', 68945, 0), (471577, 'The truth is, I never travel without cash. I always take a few tens with me in case of an emergency. There''s never been an emergency, and in time, I realized that Americans don''t want to touch customers'' dirty bills. They also don''t want to touch your credit card: you have to put it through the machine yourself, with your own fingers.', 68456, 0), (471578, 'If you look at human society, it is very easy, of course, to compare our warfare and territoriality with the chimpanzee. But that''s only one side of what we do. We also trade, we intermarry, we allow each other to travel through our territory. There''s an enormous amount of cooperation.', 13748, 0), (471579, 'I travel all the time.', 5456, 0), (471580, 'Each day as I travel through downtown Tucson, I am amazed at how quickly the most ancient of human behaviors have changed. For as long as there have been Homo sapiens - roughly 200,000 years - people have filled their lives principally with two activities: talking directly with other people, and doing physical things.', 5974, 0), (471581, 'Fiction leaves us so much work to do, allows the individual so much input; you have to see, you have to hear, you have to taste the madeleine, and while you are seemingly passive in your chair, you have to travel.', 6191, 0), (471582, 'I grew up in Harlem in New York, very rough, urban environment, and so what I found is that, if I can have kids travel to different places, countries, areas, it can expand their minds.', 69748, 0), (471583, 'The photograph reverses the purpose of travel, which until now had been to encounter the strange and unfamiliar.', 2728, 0), (471584, 'My ''go to'' workout is called the Asylum from Beach Body. It''s intense training with lots of intervals, core work. It''s hard! I travel a lot, so I can take it on the road with me and do it in a hotel room.', 68124, 0), (471585, 'My father is 100% Japanese and came to the United States when he was only 18 years old. My grandmother still resides in Japan, which has allowed me to travel to the roots of my ancestors with my father.', 68124, 0), (471586, 'I was told by so many people that I wouldn''t succeed because I was too different. Ironically, the very reason that people watch my channel and travel thousands of miles to see a show... is because it''s different. God didn''t send us to Earth to just blend in. We are here to share what makes us unique.', 22683, 0), (471587, 'Radical Islamic jihadists have a long-term vision. And if they have to stay in Europe to obtain a citizenship, to ultimately travel to the United States, and if it takes them five years or ten years, they''re okay with that. History has proven that.', 72131, 0), (471588, 'Traveling, you realize that differences are lost: each city takes to resembling all cities, places exchange their form, order, distances, a shapeless dust cloud invades the continents.', 504, 0), (471589, 'When I write, I''m still imagining a kid reading it on paper. I read e-books when I travel, but in general I still prefer holding an old-fashioned book in my hands. There''s a special, tactile experience.', 80, 0), (471590, 'I''ve always liked the idea that writing is a form of travel. And I started my writing career as a mystery novelist for adults.', 80, 0), (471591, 'I live a good life but a pretty simply life. I just store all my money under my mattress. My wife and I travel, and I bought my dream car, the Cobra.', 69751, 0), (471592, 'Mr. Trump of course feels sorry for what the Khan family has gone through, just, frankly, as he felt sorry for the victims that spoke before the Republican Convention who lost loved ones from illegal immigrant criminals coming in and being able to travel the country freely.', 73771, 0), (471593, 'My school didn''t have a drama department. I was one of the lucky four children who got to travel twice a week to another school because our school could only afford one taxi.', 69307, 0), (471594, 'Good Viking genes, being vegetarian and having rowdy dogs and kids definitely keep me in shape. Not eating meat gives me the energy I need to keep up with work, family and travel - I''m very active.', 26624, 0), (471595, 'Fashion pictures show people looking glamorous. Travel pictures show a place looking at its best, nothing to do with the reality. In the cookery pages, the food always looks amazing, right? Most of the pictures we consume are propaganda.', 70574, 0), (471596, 'As we travel around Britain, I am convinced most of us cannot really appreciate what we are seeing. We take too much for granted, because it is all so familiar.', 70574, 0), (471597, 'By default, I am a travel photographer. I work on a combination of commissions and personal projects that take me around the world.', 70574, 0), (471598, 'For those aspiring to make a living from travel photography, it''s a sad fact that the boring shots are the shots that are going to make you money.', 70574, 0), (471599, 'In this life, you should read everything you can read. Taste everything you can taste. Meet everyone you can meet. Travel everywhere you can travel. Learn everything you can learn. Experience everything you can experience.', 8855, 0), (471600, 'I stepped away to find out more about myself, which I was having difficulty doing as a football player. I got a chance to travel the world. I studied Eastern philosophy, and I''ve grown as a person so much.', 69753, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471601, 'Texts and e-mails travel no faster than phone calls and telegrams, and their content isn''t necessarily richer or poorer.', 20620, 0), (471602, 'I always try to travel light.', 30169, 0), (471603, 'I travel a lot. I''m on the move.', 34846, 0), (471604, 'I sit here as the first African-American attorney general, serving the first African-American President of the United States. And that has to show that we have made a great deal of progress. But there''s still more we have to travel along this road so we get to the place that is consistent with our founding ideals.', 71441, 0), (471605, 'There''s an image that some of us have of Jackie Onassis, stepping out in the rain, and Maurice Tempelsman is holding her umbrella. We want that man. We want the man to be the concierge and the masseur and the travel booker.', 70445, 0), (471606, 'From a pretty early age, I developed an interest in travel. I told my parents I wanted to live abroad, and they said, ''Well, you have to have money to do those things.''', 68291, 0), (471607, 'What I like about modelling is that it has given me that opportunity to travel and experience different cultures, work with creative people, and now it''s given me a voice, and with that voice hopefully I can do good things with it.', 18360, 0), (471608, 'There was never any question that I would go to college, that I would travel, that I would go to the theater early and often.', 67678, 0), (471609, 'The bottom line is, if you''re pregnant, don''t travel to an area where Zika is spreading.', 67068, 0), (471610, 'The first case of Ebola diagnosed in the United States has caused some to call on the United States to ban travel for anyone from the countries in West Africa facing the worst of the Ebola epidemic. That response is understandable. It''s only human to want to protect ourselves and our families.', 67068, 0), (471611, 'I''m obsessed with Nicholas Sparks. I''ve literally read every single book, because every time I travel, at the airport, I always buy a new Nicholas Sparks book.', 61453, 0), (471612, 'The trains that travel the Chunnel are massive machines. The Eurostars are bullet-shaped and a quarter-mile long. They are pulled by a 136,000-pound locomotive and move in the open air at 185 m.p.h. and through the tunnel at 100 m.p.h.', 72133, 0), (471613, 'When I was 17, my main goal was to be in a band and travel the world. I ended up getting to do that with my old band Hey Monday. I got to see the world and learn how to tour, and the next thing I knew, I was on ''The Voice.'' So it was just a crazy, crazy ride.', 74290, 0), (471614, 'I travel around the world constantly promoting my projects and endorsing products. Yes, I do get paid to go to parties; in fact, I''m the person who started the whole trend of paid appearances. But when you see me at a party, I''m always working or promoting something.', 50391, 0), (471615, 'When I go on Japanese Airlines, I really love it because I like Japanese food.', 11398, 0), (471616, 'There''s this group online that I frequent. It''s a group of prop crazies just like me called the Replica Props Forum, and it''s people who trade, make and travel in information about movie props.', 11175, 0), (471617, 'When we set out our original program from the beginning, obviously our markets were pretty limited, and we were thinking about them mostly as U.S. shows, and they would travel like other U.S. shows have.', 68951, 0), (471618, 'Most people travel with a good book, but I also keep my agenda with me; I''ll flip through the pages and take a few moments to organize my life a little - I rarely get the time to do this normally.', 71247, 0), (471619, 'I didn''t have any expectations of what my family life would end up being like. But I''ve been very blessed in my life to have a wife who loves me and supports me and is able to be in my band and travel with me.', 69758, 0), (471620, 'My first full year of touring, I did 300 days on the road. That was not including the travel time or publicity or anything else - that was just dates. I was home probably less than 50 days that year.', 69758, 0), (471621, 'We travel so much as touring musicians and artists that sometimes, when you hear a great song that you really think could be on your project, you go ahead and record it instead of try to write it.', 67876, 0), (471622, 'I think having toured the world and seeing many places, I''ve just been blown away by how we''ve really scarred our home. I''m as guilty as the next person if not more so. I travel a lot. The damage we do to our planet is huge.', 16022, 0), (471623, 'I''m always ready for the enemy to come over the hill. I''m packed and set to go. That comes from my time in the army. I used to travel in a tank, but now it''s a tour bus going to safer places.', 16022, 0), (471624, 'Not everything in old age is grim. I haven''t walked through an airport for years, and wheelchairs are the way to travel.', 9086, 0), (471625, 'I''m vegan on home base, but when I travel to other countries, I throw it all into the garbage.', 70264, 0), (471626, 'I think part of what I love about being an actor is getting to take on different worlds and investigate different genres and travel to different lands.', 70264, 0), (471627, 'I''ve always been a big fan of time travel, and I''m very into the notion that some day we''ll be able to do it. Beam me up!', 66597, 0), (471628, 'I hope that I''ll be hot for a long time so I can make a lot of money, I can retire early, and just travel. Hopefully that will happen.', 68954, 0), (471629, 'I live in Chicago, but my work is always in New York or L.A., so I always have to travel for my job.', 68954, 0), (471630, 'I love the idea that if you''re going to travel through time, you do it in this insanely dangerous car travelling at 88 miles per hour.', 5971, 0), (471631, 'I was destined to work with dying patients. I had no choice when I encountered my first AIDS patient. I felt called to travel some 250,000 miles each year to hold workshops that helped people cope with the most painful aspects of life, death and the transition between the two.', 1080, 0), (471632, 'Horror movies travel pretty well anyway. They''re like action movies: People overseas can watch them and enjoy them, and they''re not so culturally specific in terms of their references, and they can follow a good scary story.', 10386, 0), (471633, 'Death by plane crash scares me. I travel a lot, and when you hit turbulence, and post 9/11, that''s in the back of my mind a bit.', 10386, 0), (471634, 'Even with protection, even with death threats, I can publish, I can travel and I can live the life that I want and not the one my parents want or some imam somewhere thinks I should live.', 1135, 0), (471635, 'I always want to give my best and do the best I can. I know when I have sung my best and when I haven''t. There can be stresses and hassles with time travel and press attention. I just have to adapt and find a way of dealing with it.', 70062, 0), (471636, 'In Heaven, I believe my dad is somewhere doing something nice. I feel I''ve been too lucky to travel this far without somebody guiding me.', 70062, 0), (471637, 'It''s shocking to think about how little the travel industry cares about sustainability - and it''s the basis of their business!', 67073, 0), (471638, 'We may regard the solar systems as separate sponges, swimming in a World of Divine Spirit, and thus it will be apparent that in order to travel from one solar system to another, it would be necessary to be able to function consciously in the highest vehicle of man, the Divine Spirit.', 22756, 0), (471639, 'I think all regions have had their peculiarities of speech rounded off by television, radio, and people travel so much more now.', 24382, 0), (471640, 'All the rappers my age are getting Audemars and Rolexes. I want to find my own thing. That''s why I travel the world - for me, that''s my B-side, why we go places. I have a Hublot on from time to time but I want a home base watch - something that''s elegant but has got a little pizzazz to it.', 69358, 0), (471641, 'My first experiences of Colorado travel have been rather severe. At Greeley, I got a small upstairs room at first, but gave it up to a married couple with a child, and then had one downstairs no bigger than a cabin, with only a canvas partition. It was very hot, and every place was thick with black flies.', 68866, 0), (471642, 'I particularly like to travel for work because you see a completely different side of the country you''re visiting.', 66935, 0), (471643, 'The growth of purposeful travel is a good thing. It can have a positive impact. We should continue to experiment and move along this line.', 74131, 0), (471644, 'Travel is an exercise partly in broadening yourself and partly in defining your own limits.', 572, 0), (471645, 'I started traveling out of curiosity, but I have come to believe in travel''s political importance, that encouraging a nation''s citizenry to travel may be as important as encouraging school attendance, environmental conservation, or national thrift. You cannot understand the otherness of places you have not encountered.', 572, 0), (471646, 'You can''t expect the entire world to come to New York to see you. You have to travel to them.', 44675, 0), (471647, 'I realized I couldn''t have one foot in the fiction world and one foot in the nonfiction world, which is why ''Here I Go Again'' is so not me. I didn''t graduate from high school in the ''90s, I never listened to metal music, and I don''t time travel.', 2325, 0), (471648, 'Michael Palin decided to give up on his considerable comedy talents to make those dreadfully tedious travel shows. Have you ever tried to watch one?', 8174, 0), (471649, 'Touring can be tough; the crew and I travel everywhere by a big pink bus, and live in petrol stations.', 68466, 0), (471650, 'I''m a ''tweener,'' man! I couldn''t march with Dr. King and them. And I''m too old to be a hip-hopper. But I''ve been granted honorary status in each generation... I see my tongue as a bridge over which ideas can travel back and forth.', 3861, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471651, 'Big climbs energize me. It''s all the other aspects of being a pro-climber that wear me down. The travel and expeditions and training can become pretty tiring. But the actual big climbs - that''s what I live for.', 69700, 0), (471652, 'I travel around and hear from so many kids. Their parents say they were always very picky but they watch the show and they want to try stuff. The show is entertainment, but I think it has done so much for the public perception of what food can be.', 71877, 0), (471653, 'Since I travel so much, it''s always great to be home. There''s nothing like getting to raid my own refrigerator at two in the morning.', 64661, 0), (471654, 'Being in the pop group Eternal gave me the most wonderful opportunity to travel the world, and I have visited some spectacular countries.', 73212, 0), (471655, 'The genre has moved into this commercial aspect of itself, and ignored this extraordinarily rich literature that''s filed everywhere else except under travel.', 18322, 0), (471656, 'The truth is I''m not really interested in travel writing as it''s generally conceived, and even less so in female travel writing.', 18322, 0), (471657, 'Every congresswoman surely endures the same strains that drive some of her male colleagues to have affairs: lots of travel, families far away, heady work that makes a domestic routine seem distant and boring. But the stakes are much higher for women, because they are still judged by a different standard.', 28478, 0), (471658, 'Once you''re in a room like ''30 Rock,'' it''s a creative setting, so you write more even after you go home, just because you''re still in that mode of coming up with jokes. So the job wasn''t sapping standup jokes, but it was sapping stand up time and energy, and I wouldn''t be able to travel as much.', 69726, 0), (471659, 'I think that you certainly don''t have to be aged and travel the world to write a poem.', 9002, 0), (471660, 'In a certain sense, a writer is an exile, an outsider, always reporting on things, and it is part of his life to keep on the move. Travel is natural.', 9834, 0), (471661, 'I love anywhere new and different. That''s the fun of travel. I''ve always loved driving through Spain, France and Italy - sometimes in an Alfa Spider.', 68788, 0), (471662, 'I''ve always traveled, as a kid my parents moved me around, a different place in Germany every four years. But I got the travel bug when I was a kid, living in different countries.', 45050, 0), (471663, 'I''ve been fortunate enough to write a book and travel the country to sign and sell it, so I can safely say that a five-second burst of conversation while you''re scribbling your name, over and over, is not the most reliable way to bond with Americans.', 71157, 0), (471664, 'I hate to travel. I don''t go anywhere.', 3396, 0), (471665, 'The idea of making access to safe abortions harder and more expensive and more difficult, having to travel across state lines - that puts women''s health and lives in jeopardy, which is something I think no one wants.', 70693, 0), (471666, 'The Nike Fuel Band is interesting - it measures your movements and how far you''ve walked and how hard you''ve worked that day. I prefer using when I travel. It''s a fun way to see how far I''ve walked - how many steps I''ve taken when I''m walking around different cities.', 69725, 0), (471667, 'I travel a lot, and that makes it harder to date, but it also opens up opportunities for me to meet people where I wouldn''t normally meet them.', 70063, 0), (471668, 'I travel fairly lightly because you have to these days. I always take a laptop and an iPod so I can watch movies and listen to music. And my Gameboy. That''s a good time-killer.', 74291, 0), (471669, 'In my 20s, as I began to travel in Europe, I found comfort in religious paintings. Even though my own belief in Catholic dogma had been shaken and weakened, I found that the beauty and the richness of the art still held me.', 27793, 0), (471670, 'Eating well was something I learned as I started to be successful and had to travel and perform concerts, which are an intense cardio workout.', 68146, 0), (471671, 'Because travel has always been such a vital part of myself and so essential to who I am, I have made the decision to continue to put myself back out into the world. And that''s not an easy decision to make.', 16246, 0), (471672, 'Getting on a plane is hard for me, but I do it, because travel is vital to me.', 16246, 0), (471673, 'I don''t like to travel. Yet all my books seem to involve a journey.', 42273, 0), (471674, 'The railroads needed standardized time; as a result, the technology of train travel shaped the way everyone gets up, eats, goes to sleep, calculates age, and, perhaps of no small importance, imagine the world as a whole, ticking reliably, with reliable deviations, according to the beat of one central clock in a physical location.', 69142, 0), (471675, 'As a child I sometimes used to travel to the West Bank to visit my family, so I know what the checkpoints felt like. I knew what it was like to live under occupation.', 67571, 0), (471676, 'I try to travel as light as possible to avoid baggage issues. Los Angeles airport is notorious for baggage delays, so I''ll often FedEx a suitcase ahead or back so I don''t need to stand around; it also minimises problems at check-in.', 71303, 0), (471677, 'You don''t have to travel, but I find extended travel to be a helpful tool for reexamining yourself and the constraints you''ve artificially placed on your life. It''s easy to believe everything has to be done one way if you''re always in one place around the same people.', 11201, 0), (471678, 'I knew from the first moment I picked up a camera, on my first school assignment, what I wanted to do for the rest of my life. I was going to find a way to travel the world and tell the stories of the people I met through photographs.', 68218, 0), (471679, 'During prom season, I travel around the country with a 20-by-24 camera - which is logistically complicated - and photograph proms. My husband made a film of it.', 68218, 0), (471680, 'When I travel with my kids abroad, I am not myself, but I''m more a father who wants to protect them. Sometimes, I am even aggressive about certain things and get surprised seeing myself like that: for instance, when people want to take pictures of them. I am fine if they want to take my pictures, but they are not public property.', 66442, 0), (471681, 'Being able to travel the world is pretty cool. There are places that I''ve always wanted to go to but being able to go there as somebody who''s a musician and is recognised as one is cool.', 72755, 0), (471682, 'Travel books are, by and large, boring. They lodge uncomfortably between fact, fiction and autobiography.', 70697, 0), (471683, 'Occasionally I find a travel book that is both illuminating and entertaining, where vivid writing and research replace self-indulgence and sloppy prose.', 70697, 0), (471684, 'Don Quixote''s ''Delusions'' is an excellent read - far better than my own forthcoming travel book, ''Walking Backwards Across Tuscany.''', 70697, 0), (471685, 'Scoring goals is the best feeling you can have. I always look up at the stand for my family straight afterwards it means everything to me that they travel to every game. ', 47161, 0), (471686, 'There are always things I find difficult - being in crowds, remembering faces. I do like routines. I always travel with someone. My life in Avignon is a very quiet one. I have an apartment that looks over the whole city. I can drop into town, but a lot of the time I write from home. In some respects I still live a very quiet, simple life.', 11921, 0), (471687, 'In the spring of 1968, The Beatles and I were invited by Maharishi Mahesh Yogi to travel to Riskikesh, India. Riskikesh has been an important spiritual place to many millions of people over the years. It is situated where the Ganges River flows out of the Himalayas, and to be in that atmosphere was something incredibly special.', 66962, 0), (471688, 'With all the stuff that''s going on in the world - after I watch the news, read the news, and listen to my podcasts, at the end of the day, am I really going to watch an episode of murder and time travel?', 74292, 0), (471689, 'I certainly have routines in my day-to-day life that are important to me and still give me feelings of security and control, but the capacity to break out of them every so often as I travel has given me a second wind.', 11921, 0), (471690, 'Nobody controls me. I travel with my husband when I can, when I know that I can go, and I know that my son is okay alone for a few days with the help.', 67092, 0), (471691, 'Those are the kinds of roles you can really sink your teeth into. Characters with an edge. When you''re playing someone who''s sort of seedy, there''s less limitation, there''s so much space you can travel. There''s room to move in.', 68476, 0), (471692, 'We take so many of our freedoms for granted nowadays - I can travel where I like, I can have a baby when I like, I can do any job I want - but I do think chivalry has been lost a little bit.', 31314, 0), (471693, '''What comes next?'' is the constant question I''m asked by outsiders eager to travel to the island. During the eleven years I traveled to Havana, very few Cubans I met on the island ever bothered to verbalize this question.', 56442, 0), (471694, 'For years, I had no time for exploratory travel.', 45141, 0), (471695, 'Having to travel so much plays havoc with your personal life.', 45141, 0), (471696, 'I am always exhausted; I am always trying to find more time to be with my family, which is why they travel with me so much.', 68113, 0), (471697, 'Everyone carries his own inch rule of taste, and amuses himself by applying it, triumphantly, wherever he travels.', 2796, 0), (471698, 'I hate to travel with stuff.', 57401, 0), (471699, 'I''ve always been into visual effects. It was something I took keen interest in before films happened. Ironically, I am a part of ''Raaz 3,'' a film that is shot entirely on 3D. It has encouraged me to pursue my dream. Hopefully, if time permits, I will travel to the United States and attend a crash course in visual graphics and animation.', 69490, 0), (471700, 'I live in a Moomin house in East London which I fill with blankets and nice crockery and get people round for dinner. When you travel a lot, you feel rootless and adrift - this is my sanctuary, where I can breathe out.', 69519, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471701, 'If you play the same club every week of every month, it''s kind of boring. It''s great that you can play one night in Brazil and one night in Japan, one night in Europe, and see the world. It''s amazing what you see if you travel around the world.', 69210, 0), (471702, 'You must know that Iran has a great number of productions. Many films are released. Most of them, like in the rest of the world, are commercial and shallow films. These are the most popular ones. And there are a few ones that actually develop more profound and thoughtful aspects of life. Only some of these films travel out of Iran.', 67520, 0), (471703, 'I like playing tennis. I''ve always enjoyed the process of being a tennis player; I''m just not sure that I enjoyed the travel at the end, and my body didn''t recover from the day-to-day grind.', 67530, 0), (471704, 'It''s a very immersive and intense form of travel to walk around with an interpreter and stop random people on the street and ask them about their lives.', 26863, 0), (471705, 'We all become great explorers during our first few days in a new city, or a new love affair.', 1932, 0), (471706, 'I never travel without my Stetson, but the more I wear it the more I realise that no one wears hats any more. When I was a kid everybody wore hats, especially in Texas, but I get off the plane in Dallas now and I''m the only guy with a hat. It''s amazing.', 64769, 0), (471707, 'Touch seems to be such an important tool for enhancing social cooperation and affiliation that we have evolved a special physical route along which those subliminal feelings of social connection travel from skin to brain.', 26113, 0), (471708, 'My father''s plan was, we were going to grow up and travel the world.', 70918, 0), (471709, 'I travel all over the country speaking to young people, and I am always amazed at how engaged in environmental conservation they are.', 70918, 0), (471710, 'I''ve said before, the number one thing that we have to work on is protecting the gay community from sharia law. Now, in the United States, it''s probably not a big issue right now, but my brother-in-law is gay, and his partner and I would like them to be able to travel any place in the world without them risking harm.', 68481, 0), (471711, 'I want my life to match my work now. I don''t want to work and then travel. I want to be at one place.', 69720, 0), (471712, 'Our career is a dream. I mean, we get to act, travel around the world, and meet cool people. What''s not to love!', 66806, 0), (471713, 'Doing Shakespeare once is not fair to the play. I have been in Shakespeare plays when it''s not until the last two or three performances when I even understand certain things. In the old days star actors would travel the world doing the same parts over and over again.', 761, 0), (471714, 'Chess has given me a lot more than I could ask for. I have been able to feel special, travel the world and do what I truly enjoy. Moreover, chess players love being their own boss and hate having to wake up early!', 72572, 0), (471715, 'The good news is that real-world hands-on conservation is alive and well and catching on across the America I travel.', 68760, 0), (471716, 'When I travel abroad, because I''m Columbian, I''m always one that they check twice and security and I''m the one that they open my bag and the one they pull to the side to check the visa.', 70531, 0), (471717, 'I remember returning to Bangalore after a few months of travel and seeing it as a first-world city, like New York or San Francisco. This may be obvious to some people, but I grew up in Delhi, and I had no experience of how someone from a ''Tier 2'' city may view a ''Tier 1'' city. You really do emigrate between worlds when you come from those towns.', 15932, 0), (471718, 'I''ve been lucky enough to travel widely. When you''re based in Europe, it''s very easy to go to Madrid or Budapest for the weekend. I also lived in Italy for ten years and now live in Ireland.', 45413, 0), (471719, 'If you travel 11 months a year - from one dangerous or isolated situation to the next - if you live in hotels, and every relationship with another human being is a two-week relationship, the only other people who have any idea what you''re going through or how strung out you are are other photographers.', 74293, 0), (471720, 'I find Facebook absolutely fascinating because I don''t think there''s ever been any one source that had so much information about each of us - who we talk to, who our friends are, what books we read, what we''re buying, what movies we saw, what our travel is.', 74293, 0), (471721, 'I have just returned from Boston. It is the only thing to do if you find yourself up there.', 13077, 0), (471722, 'In the Arctic, the Inuit are saying water and land are the same; they''re an unbroken unity. In the winter, you travel on the ice because it''s the linkage and the easiest way, and in the summer, you move around on the water.', 30260, 0), (471723, 'Novels set in distant places give us expectations not unlike those we have of travel writing, and often the distinctions are blurred, as in, say, the way the low life of Tokyo''s Shinjuku Ward is depicted in John David Morley''s recent ''Pictures from the Water Trade.''', 23303, 0), (471724, 'I love short trips to New York to me it is the finest three-day town on earth. ', 3628, 0), (471725, 'No matter where I''ve been overseas, the food stinks, except in Italy.', 67099, 0), (471726, 'Traveling is seeing it is the implicit that we travel by. ', 30964, 0), (471727, 'I''m a travel enthusiast.', 22869, 0), (471728, 'I like to travel in jeans because I don''t want to wallow around in my suit, you know? They cost too much. Jeans are comfortable.', 71178, 0), (471729, 'It really is a fact that liberals are much higher than conservatives on a major personality trait called ''openness to experience.'' People who are high on openness to experience just crave novelty, variety, diversity, new ideas, travel. People low on it like things that are familiar, that are safe and dependable.', 2838, 0), (471730, 'I did rebel. I was the rebel in my family, because my dad wanted me to go and just travel with him.', 74294, 0), (471731, 'A man who leaves home to mend himself and others is a philosopher; but he who goes from country to country, guided by the blind impulse of curiosity, is a vagabond.', 2204, 0), (471732, 'I''d rather have huge success and huge failures than travel in the middle of the road.', 18673, 0), (471733, 'Every time I took a long leave from home, I felt as if I were going to conquer the world. Or rather, take possession of what is my birthright, my inheritance.', 70829, 0), (471734, 'In America there are two classes of travel - first class, and with children.', 2188, 0), (471735, 'I want to travel around the country and make my living playing music. I also try to behave in a way that I would appreciate as a music fan. That''s how we conduct ourselves, be it in writing music or playing it live.', 67119, 0), (471736, 'You become a better writer by writing. You become a better travel writer by writing about travel.', 26945, 0), (471737, 'When I travel I normally eat club sandwiches or I bring my own food. When you go into a new town, it''s very had to find a good place to eat.', 72287, 0), (471738, 'My writing is a combination of three elements. The first is travel: not travel like a tourist, but travel as exploration. The second is reading literature on the subject. The third is reflection.', 9900, 0), (471739, 'The perfect pop song is a 20th-century creation; it''s not a sonnet, it''s not an opera, it''s something short - three and a half minutes by nature - and has this ability to travel and to defy class and economic structures.', 69531, 0), (471740, 'Actually, I started to become an actress because I met someone who was just a friend and I found his life wonderful, I thought, Oh my god, you can travel, you''re free, you can do what you want, you''re the boss. And then I met an actor and I was in love with him.', 67721, 0), (471741, 'Whether a plane to Singapore, a subway in Manhattan, or the streets of Cincinnati, I search for meaningful conversation wherever I may travel. Without it, I believe we lose the ability to not only understand others, but more importantly, ourselves.', 20109, 0), (471742, 'Every day is intense and alive, whether it''s travel, work, even down time, which there is so little of.', 74295, 0), (471743, 'The worst thing about touring is the travel.', 67145, 0), (471744, 'When I was little, I didn''t really travel - from the suburbs to Paris was already a journey. I had a foreigner''s eye on the city, and I still enjoy that point of view. Then there''s the fact that one of the things that touches me most is injustice.', 74296, 0), (471745, 'I always thought when I hit 50 years old that''d be it for the travel. I don''t have to tell you - you wait at an airport, your flight''s delayed, get on a 14-hour flight, get off, get stuck in traffic, you get to the hotel and the room service is closed.', 74297, 0), (471746, 'To get away from one''s working environment is, in a sense, to get away from one''s self; and this is often the chief advantage of travel and change.', 37070, 0), (471747, 'Greater personal choice, individually tailored services, stronger local accountability, greater efficiency - these are all central to the new direction of travel we have set for our public services.', 66758, 0), (471748, 'Movie acting is a great job for your twenties: You travel all over, you have affairs with people, and you throw yourself into one part and then another. It gets more challenging as you get older, and it''s not just having a daughter, it''s wanting to have your own life and be yourself.', 74298, 0), (471749, 'The only thing I like about air travel is it gives me time to read.', 17696, 0), (471750, 'Rail travel for me is the most relaxing, most scenic way to see the country.', 66576, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471751, 'I wanted to do my part to help preserve that golden age of travel... I step aboard The Patron Tequila Express railcar, and I go back in time to the days when a long journey was something fun and very special.', 66576, 0), (471752, 'I''ve always enjoyed traveling and having experience with different cultures and different people. But it''s also a wonderful thing to be able to benefit and enable research, not only in our country but around the world.', 67588, 0), (471753, 'I''m passionate and I travel the world not just as a tourist but to understand cultures... I''ve lived with Masai tribe... I travel the world and bring it back in the form of a research book that would become the starting point for the collection.', 72906, 0), (471754, 'I travel a lot, but I don''t come away with new inspiration.', 74299, 0), (471755, 'As an actor, I travel around a lot and live in a lot of hotels, and many times I''ve been in a town where the only entertainment to be had is what you find in the hotel bar or lobby.', 67921, 0), (471756, 'You discover how confounding the world is when you try to draw it. You look at a car, and you try to see its car-ness, and you''re like an immigrant to your own world. You don''t have to travel to encounter weirdness. You wake up to it.', 26433, 0), (471757, 'But I want people to understand that poker''s not all glamorous, it''s not all being on TV and making tons of money. It''s a hard life. It''s a lot of travel. It''s a lot of weird hours.', 74300, 0), (471758, 'I mean, the first ''Back to the Future'' is kind of a perfect script, I think, in terms of handling time travel the best. It depends on your definition. To me, that means it effectively uses it in the story.', 71600, 0), (471759, 'My parents and my grandfather on my mom''s side would travel the earth. They went to Australia and China, and they went to probably every soccer game I ever played.', 69650, 0), (471760, 'I still don''t have a car. I still travel by public transport. I take autos to travel to and fro for recordings.', 68310, 0), (471761, 'For years, I had a top secret clearance and never left Russia. Just once did I go to Bulgaria with my wife for a holiday at the Golden Sands resort, but I could not mention my real name. I was allowed to travel abroad only in the early 1990s.', 74301, 0), (471762, 'When Bangladesh refused to renew my passport, I used U.N. travel documents. You can''t disown your country.', 10634, 0), (471763, 'Then I was lucky I met with my future husband, and I started new life with my husband, and I was happy again. He was a musician. I start to travel with him through Europe also and around the former Soviet Union.', 74302, 0), (471764, 'I always travel with my guitar. I take it myself - with me in my hand. I don''t like to send it by cargo because it''s dangerous. There is no way I would do that.', 67930, 0), (471765, 'The hardest part is to travel, and to be away from your family.', 74303, 0), (471766, 'My wife and I have so much fun when we travel and find anything... like stray cats and squirrels.', 74304, 0), (471767, 'Travel is very subjective. What one person loves, another loathes.', 66645, 0), (471768, 'I don''t think I could have a genuine relationship with someone who didn''t love to travel and appreciate new foods. Traveling is a big part of my life, and I want to share that with the people close to me.', 74305, 0), (471769, 'For the Trump brand name, when we build, we want only the best buildings in the world. We travel a lot to see real estate projects worldwide, and we always study what can be done better. There''s no question about it: a Trump Tower has to have the very best quality, amenities and facilities. People want that ultra-luxurious lifestyle.', 74306, 0), (471770, 'One of the perks of my job as a fashion journalist is the travel opportunity.', 69565, 0), (471771, 'I want to explore a new place each year, and it can be within India. When I was shooting for ''Mohenjo Daro'', I couldn''t travel out of the country for two years. But it gave me an opportunity to explore new places within India. I''m sure there are so many places to explore in India, and I would love to go there.', 68127, 0), (471772, 'On reflection, I am always pleasantly surprised when ordinary members of the public stop me in the street to say, ''Thank you,'' I guess for making travel and other goods and services affordable to them.', 72080, 0), (471773, 'I was born to travel and write verse.', 4453, 0), (471774, 'Travel is the best and probably cheapest graduate school you can buy.', 70575, 0), (471775, 'Singing is my passion and I always wanted to travel the country.', 71783, 0), (471776, 'Travel is the frivolous part of serious lives, and the serious part of frivolous ones.', 73291, 0), (471777, 'I say that I get paid to travel, and I play the shows for free.', 74307, 0), (471778, 'I like the opportunity to travel the world and work in close company with other people.', 69577, 0), (471779, 'On long haul flights I always drink loads and loads of water and eat light and healthy food.', 66844, 0), (471780, 'As many of you know I travel a good bit and do not get to see my friends and family as much as I would like.', 70554, 0), (471781, 'Sometimes you just want to get away and be normal for a few days. It''s a treat to travel without your racket bag.', 72081, 0), (471782, 'The time to enjoy a European trip is about three weeks after unpacking.', 9905, 0), (471783, 'High-speed rail would revolutionise interstate travel and would also be an economic game-changer for dozens of regional communities along its path.', 74308, 0), (471784, 'I myself believe that there will one day be time travel because when we find that something isn''t forbidden by the over-arching laws of physics we usually eventually find a technological way of doing it.', 13526, 0), (471785, 'I get pretty much all the exercise I need walking down airport concourses carrying bags.', 16932, 0), (471786, 'As you think, you travel, and as you love, you attract. You are today where your thoughts have brought you; you will be tomorrow where your thoughts take you.', 14092, 0), (471787, 'Normally, it takes me about three years to write one of the big books. It is usually four years between releases because of the huge amount of travel and PR and just nuisance going on around them. I have a lot of pressure from publishers and agents.', 74286, 0), (471788, 'For young girls, whom I meet a lot when I travel around the country, it will be a big thing. It will really show them that there''s no post in Denmark that a girl can''t aspire to.', 74309, 0), (471789, 'The biggest luxury is a job in which I get to live in New York, travel the world, and work with so many incredible people.', 69227, 0), (471790, 'I''m not a DJ, I don''t know how to scratch and I don''t know how to mix, but I do know how to party. One of my jobs is actually to travel the world and party.', 69920, 0), (471791, 'Air travel survived decades of terrorism, including attacks which resulted in the deaths of everyone on the plane. It survived 9/11. It''ll survive the next successful attack. The only real worry is that we''ll scare ourselves into making air travel so onerous that we won''t fly anymore.', 25686, 0), (471792, 'I don''t travel anywhere without the PS3 and XBox. There''s nothing better to do on long bus trips while on tour.', 70141, 0), (471793, 'I get to travel, see the world, meet people and be independent. I feel blessed.', 74310, 0), (471794, 'I''m a painter, really. To be successful, you have to go to Hollywood, and I didn''t like to travel.', 67369, 0), (471795, 'I travel often, so my routine is always getting scrambled. But on a standard sort of day, I get up at 6, pack lunches, hustle the kids off to school, then brew a pot of coffee and head downstairs to the dungeon, as I call it: my cobwebby office in the basement.', 22321, 0), (471796, 'For people to understand me when I travel, I speak with my hands.', 74311, 0), (471797, 'I would like to host a show, something like travel or cooking or something like that, something I''m really interested in, and so I''m pitching a couple television shows.', 69804, 0), (471798, 'Since traveling is such a big part of my life when I am working, I like to vacation relatively close to home. Florida is a great place for me to go and relax. It''s so close, which is perfect because it''s the minimal travel time.', 71994, 0), (471799, 'The attention of a traveller, should be particularly turned, in the first place, to the various works of Nature, to mark the distinctions of the climates he may explore, and to offer such useful observations on the different productions as may occur.', 68071, 0), (471800, 'Two great talkers will not travel far together.', 21461, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471801, 'Wherever we go, across the Pacific or Atlantic, we meet, not similarity so much as ''the bizarre''. Things astonish us, when we travel, that surprise nobody else.', 64286, 0), (471802, 'The gift of sobriety is clarity and a sense of connection - and travel only enhances that.', 5860, 0), (471803, 'My first ever job after college was as a flight attendant. I wanted to travel and could not afford it, so I decided to get myself a job where I could travel. I did it for two years and had great fun.', 1999, 0), (471804, 'I think it''s important to travel around in order to get a notion of what''s going on, to find out what people are think about. I enjoy talking on campuses most because people are more informed and discussion is generally livelier.', 73552, 0), (471805, 'All I wanted was to be big, to be in show business and to travel... and that''s what I''ve been doing all my life.', 74312, 0), (471806, 'To enjoy enduring success we should travel a little in advance of the world.', 74313, 0), (471807, 'I served at the Pentagon and at Fort Leavenworth - my job was video cameraman, and that allowed me to travel to places like Korea, Japan, Alaska, Germany and the Netherlands.', 74314, 0), (471808, 'If you travel first class, you think first class and you are more likely to play first class.', 74315, 0), (471809, 'White sharks and tuna travel for thousands of miles before returning to the same hot spot just as salmon do when they return to the same stream. These journeys are the marine equivalent of wildebeest migrations that take place on the Serengeti plain in Africa.', 74316, 0), (471810, 'All my books reflect travel adventures of some kind, and all have a soul: a spiritual or mystical underpinning.', 2506, 0), (471811, 'On the whole, when I travel to different countries, I like to find the hidden places, so I tend to avoid the cities - but in terms of the ease of getting about, finding what you need, the excitement, that undercurrent of whatever you want it to be, it''s got to be London.', 74317, 0), (471812, 'Airline travel is hours of boredom interrupted by moments of stark terror.', 69828, 0), (471813, 'Soul travel can be a general expansion of awareness and knowingness or conscious experience of the heavenly worlds.', 74318, 0), (471814, 'A journey by Sea and Land, Five Hundred Miles, is not undertaken without money.', 74319, 0), (471815, 'It''s hard now to imagine that kind of travel and the daily tasks they simply took for granted. If a wagon axle broke, you had to stop and carve a new one. To cross a river, you sometimes had to build a raft.', 74320, 0), (471816, 'The purpose of human life is to serve, and to show compassion and the will to help others.', 1006, 0), (471817, 'It''s sad when someone you know becomes someone you knew.', 68, 0), (471818, 'A sympathetic friend can be quite as dear as a brother.', 395, 0), (471819, 'We should feel sorrow, but not sink under its oppression.', 819, 0), (471820, 'Flowers grow out of dark moments.', 10122, 0), (471821, 'Remember me with smiles and laughter, for that is how I will remember you all. If you can only remember me with tears, then don''t remember me at all.', 17296, 0), (471822, 'One''s life has value so long as one attributes value to the life of others, by means of love, friendship, indignation and compassion.', 477, 0), (471823, 'Grief changes shape, but it never ends.', 61050, 0), (471824, 'One might expect that the families of murder victims would be showered with sympathy and support, embraced by their communities. But in reality they are far more likely to feel isolated, fearful, and ashamed, overwhelmed by grief and guilt, angry at the criminal-justice system, and shunned by their old friends.', 21365, 0), (471825, 'It is only after one is in trouble that one realizes how little sympathy and kindness there are in the world.', 72002, 0), (471826, 'I''ve always thought of acting as more of an exercise in empathy, which is not to be confused with sympathy. You''re trying to get inside a certain emotional reality or motivational reality and try to figure out what that''s about so you can represent it.', 73682, 0), (471827, 'What is lovely never dies, But passes into other loveliness.', 5885, 0), (471828, 'The dew of compassion is a tear.', 62558, 0), (471829, 'It is a great consolation for me to remember that the Lord, to whom I had drawn near in humble and child-like faith, has suffered and died for me, and that He will look on me in love and compassion.', 611, 0), (471830, 'A sorrow''s crown of sorrow is remembering happier times.', 63203, 0), (471831, 'Come away, O human child: To the waters and the wild with a fairy, hand in hand, For the world''s more full of weeping than you can understand.', 62867, 0), (471832, 'Our trials, our sorrows, and our grieves develop us.', 4025, 0), (471833, 'I say to people who care for people who are dying, if you really love that person and want to help them, be with them when their end comes close. Sit with them - you don''t even have to talk. You don''t have to do anything but really be there with them.', 1080, 0), (471834, 'It is foolish to tear one''s hair in grief, as though sorrow would be made less by baldness.', 1306, 0), (471835, 'Let no one weep for me, or celebrate my funeral with mourning; for I still live, as I pass to and fro through the mouths of men.', 15552, 0), (471836, 'When you''re successful, people have no sympathy. Nobody wants to catch the tears of a millionaire.', 57019, 0), (471837, 'When sorrows come, they come not single spies, but in battalions.', 13, 0), (471838, 'Here bring your wounded hearts, here tell your anguish; Earth has no sorrow that Heaven cannot heal.', 790, 0), (471839, 'Truly, it is in darkness that one finds the light, so when we are in sorrow, then this light is nearest of all to us.', 418, 0), (471840, 'Children require guidance and sympathy far more than instruction.', 69118, 0), (471841, 'Interest does not tie nations together it sometimes separates them. But sympathy and understanding does unite them. ', 1970, 0), (471842, 'The knowledge that we have brother scouts working in the same uniform, to the same ends, in the same way, in all corners of the Empire, cannot but make scouts proud of their brotherhood, and cannot fail to bring them into closer sympathy.', 36714, 0), (471843, 'Sorrow is so easy to express and yet so hard to tell.', 16696, 0), (471844, 'Any other illness, any other disease that we''re faced with, there''s sympathy and understanding. We get help for those. With mental illness, our go-to is to categorize them as, ''Oh, they''re crazy,'' to belittle the problem.', 74321, 0), (471845, 'Women ought to feel a peculiar sympathy in the colored man''s wrong, for, like him, she has been accused of mental inferiority, and denied the privileges of a liberal education.', 72882, 0), (471846, 'Any mind that is capable of real sorrow is capable of good.', 3252, 0), (471847, 'To desire and expect nothing for oneself and to have profound sympathy for others is genuine holiness.', 2629, 0), (471848, 'Grief knits two hearts in closer bonds than happiness ever can and common sufferings are far stronger links than common joys. ', 3430, 0), (471849, 'Badges mean nothing in themselves, but they mark a certain achievement and they are a link between the rich and the poor. For when one girl sees a badge on a sister Scout''s arm, if that girl has won the same badge, it at once awakens an interest and sympathy between them.', 69097, 0), (471850, 'As human beings, we all have reasons for our behavior. There may be people who have certain physiological issues that dictate why they make certain choices. On the whole, though, I think we''re dictated by our structure, our past, our environment, our culture. So once you understand the patterns that shape a person, how can you not find sympathy?', 37699, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471851, 'In externals we advance with lightening express speed, in modes of thought and sympathy we lumber on in stage-coach fashion.', 1362, 0), (471852, 'True Scouts are the best friends of animals, for from living in the woods and wilds, and practising observation and tracking, they get to know more than other people about the ways and habits of birds and animals, and therefore they understand them and are more in sympathy with them.', 36714, 0), (471853, 'It''s no good being nice and young and naive. There''s no good in that at all. You''ve got to do it all yourself, and you''ve gotta learn quick. And you can''t look for sympathy either.', 14227, 0), (471854, 'Developing our sympathetic compassion is not only possible but the only reason for us to be here on earth.', 1047, 0), (471855, 'Only by joy and sorrow does a person know anything about themselves and their destiny. They learn what to do and what to avoid.', 282, 0), (471856, 'I was brought up to be sympathetic toward others.', 852, 0), (471857, 'Excess of grief for the dead is madness; for it is an injury to the living, and the dead know it not.', 3360, 0), (471858, 'Grieve and mourn for yourself not once or twice, but again and again.', 2128, 0), (471859, 'Both tears and sweat are salty, but they render a different result. Tears will get you sympathy; sweat will get you change.', 23411, 0), (471860, 'What is the meaning of ''gossip?'' Doesn''t it originate with sympathy, an interest in one''s neighbor, degenerating into idle curiosity and love of tattling? Which is worse, this habit, or keeping one''s self so absorbed intellectually as to forget the sufferings and cares of others, to lose sympathy through having too much to think about?', 7253, 0), (471861, 'No one has yet realized the wealth of sympathy, the kindness and generosity hidden in the soul of a child. The effort of every true education should be to unlock that treasure.', 805, 0), (471862, 'In fiction, imaginary people become realer to us than any named celebrity glimpsed in a series of rumored events, whose causes and subtler ramifications must remain in the dark. An invented figure like Anna Karenina or Emma Bovary emerges fully into the light of understanding, which brings with it identification, sympathy and pity.', 135, 0), (471863, 'I am really drawn to damaged characters, and I have a lot of sympathy for them. Making those complicated characters empathetic is something to strive for. It''s too easy to create a good guy or a good girl.', 18156, 0), (471864, 'The Nazi movement is in many respects one which has my warmest sympathy.', 266, 0), (471865, 'Character is made of duty and love and sympathy, and, above all, of living and working for others.', 67335, 0), (471866, 'When we are out of sympathy with the young, then I think our work in this world is over.', 3992, 0), (471867, 'I feel sympathy for the working class lad. I''ve always championed about ticket prices and try to equate that to people''s salaries.', 59447, 0), (471868, 'I tend to foster drama via bleakness. If I want the reader to feel sympathy for a character, I cleave the character in half, on his birthday. And then it starts raining. And he''s made of sugar.', 1047, 0), (471869, 'It appears to be a law that you cannot have a deep sympathy with both man and nature.', 1049, 0), (471870, 'I have several close friends who are insomniacs. Over the years, I''ve heard their stories about being up in the middle of the night, completely awake. I see them yawn at 11 A.M. and know that, regardless of what they are doing, they''d probably rather be in bed sleeping. I''ve always had sympathy for them, but I''ve never really understood it.', 66612, 0), (471871, 'The irony is that I''m actually a very empathetic person, but I don''t believe in sympathy at all.', 1860, 0), (471872, 'AIDS had won gays sympathy they no longer seemed the privileged brats that the general populace had resented in the 1970s. ', 9683, 0), (471873, 'Ultimately, we''ll help the people we discriminate against if we try to understand more about them; genetics will lead to a world where there is a sympathy for the underdog.', 13403, 0), (471874, 'Teetotallers lack the sympathy and generosity of men that drink.', 8732, 0), (471875, 'When our bodies are sick and people extend their sympathy, bring us soup, offer up solutions. When our minds are sick, people tend to shy away from you, be afraid, or call you outright crazy. I''m fascinated by the way society and individuals view mental illness, and most of my shorts comment on that.', 22054, 0), (471876, 'I have a strong sympathy for all women who have struggled and suffered.', 74322, 0), (471877, 'Almost all of our sorrows spring out of our relations with other people.', 1304, 0), (471878, 'From the end spring new beginnings.', 3240, 0), (471879, 'To all those who have suffered as a consequence of our troubled past I extend my sincere thoughts and deep sympathy. With the benefit of historical hindsight we can all see things which we would wish had been done differently or not at all.', 65677, 0), (471880, 'People who drink to drown their sorrow should be told that sorrow knows how to swim.', 3199, 0), (471881, 'After you have wept and grieved for your physical losses, cherish the functions and the life you have left.', 2128, 0), (471882, 'I''ve always liked Saturn. But I also have some sympathy for Pluto because I heard it''s been downgraded from a planet, and I think it should remain a planet. Once you''ve given something planetary status it''s kind of mean to take it away.', 5191, 0), (471883, 'I have sometimes been wildly, despairingly, acutely miserable, racked with sorrow, but through it all I still know quite certainly that just to be alive is a grand thing.', 94, 0), (471884, 'If you suppress grief too much, it can well redouble.', 1695, 0), (471885, 'I believe that we must reach our brother, never toning down our fundamental oppositions, but meeting him when he asks to be met, with a reason for the faith that is in us, as well as with a loving sympathy for them as brothers.', 848, 0), (471886, 'We Germans have a special responsibility to be alert, sensitive, and aware of what we did during the Nazi era and about lasting damage caused in other countries. I''ve got tremendous sympathy for that.', 67556, 0), (471887, 'In the early days of the Russian Revolution in 1917, I was completely in sympathy with it. I felt that it established a new era in the history of the modern world. I was so overwhelmed by it that, if people made any unfriendly comment, I would vigorously defend it. If people condemned the Communist party, I would speak in its defense.', 67633, 0), (471888, 'If you''re disabled, and you''re trying to achieve your dreams, accept the fact right now that you have to work 500 times more than the average bear next to you. Stop bucking for sympathy, put on your titanium legs, and run.', 68025, 0), (471889, 'Grief can''t be shared. Everyone carries it alone. His own burden in his own way.', 1407, 0), (471890, 'What ye have been ye still shall be, When we are dust the dust among, O yellow flowers!', 12929, 0), (471891, 'I think loss of loved ones is the hardest blow in life.', 34804, 0), (471892, 'Excessive sorrow laughs. Excessive joy weeps.', 221, 0), (471893, 'I will indulge my sorrows, and give way to all the pangs and fury of despair.', 2868, 0), (471894, 'Pity may represent little more than the impersonal concern which prompts the mailing of a check, but true sympathy is the personal concern which demands the giving of one''s soul.', 21767, 0), (471895, 'The only cure for grief is action.', 41950, 0), (471896, 'Farewell, dearest friend, never to see one another any more till at the right hand of Christ.', 68026, 0), (471897, 'Men are often biased in their judgment on account of their sympathy and their interests.', 68784, 0), (471898, 'There is something terribly morbid in the modern sympathy with pain. One should sympathise with the colour, the beauty, the joy of life. The less said about life''s sores the better.', 40, 0), (471899, 'Having a baby is a disaster for your career. I don''t think there''s any sympathy.', 67020, 0), (471900, 'Obviously, Jay-Z is one of the greatest entertainers of the world today. Not only is he a remarkable rhetorical genius, he''s also a man of deep sympathy and empathy for those who are lost and vulnerable, but especially under-educated youth of all cultures and stripes.', 3861, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471901, 'It is in our faults and failings, not in our virtues, that we touch each other, and find sympathy. It is in our follies that we are one.', 2174, 0), (471902, 'If there was less sympathy in the world, there would be less trouble in the world.', 40, 0), (471903, 'Sympathy is two hearts tugging at one load.', 42648, 0), (471904, 'The cure for sorrow is to learn something.', 30125, 0), (471905, 'The rule of friendship means there should be mutual sympathy between them, each supplying what the other lacks and trying to benefit the other, always using friendly and sincere words.', 1306, 0), (471906, 'A person who has sympathy for mankind in the lump, faith in its future progress, and desire to serve the great cause of this progress, should be called not a humanist, but a humanitarian, and his creed may be designated as humanitarianism.', 71965, 0), (471907, 'I can hardly express in words my deep feeling and sympathy for them, knowing as I do, the many serious handicaps and obstacles that will confront them in almost every walk of life.', 71342, 0), (471908, 'There''s a certain amount of sympathy here for the Bush administration''s problem, which is they would like to get rid of Saddam Hussein and they would like to have the Kurds autonomous.', 74056, 0), (471909, 'I belong to a nation which over the past centuries has experienced many hardships and reverses. The world reacted with silence or with mere sympathy when Polish frontiers were crossed by invading armies and the sovereign state had to succumb to brutal force.', 63581, 0), (471910, 'Here''s my rule: You always want to pay cash for your own books, because if they look at the name on the credit card and then they look at the name on the book jacket, then there''s this look of such profound sympathy for you that you had to resort to this. It really is withering.', 2257, 0), (471911, 'The relation of landlord and tenant is not an ideal one, but any relations in a social order will endure if there is infused into them some of that spirit of human sympathy which qualifies life for immortality.', 66713, 0), (471912, 'Women are about the best lovers of nature, after all; at least of nature in her milder and more familiar forms. The feminine character, the feminine perceptions, intuitions, delicacy, sympathy, quickness, are more responsive to natural forms and influences than is the masculine mind.', 1069, 0), (471913, 'This circus that''s advertised to show and furnish a little amusement for us heathens is owned by a woman, one whose pluck catches my sympathy every time.', 74323, 0), (471914, 'The American people want something terse, forcible, picturesque, striking - something that will arrest their attention, enlist their sympathy, arouse their indignation, stimulate their imagination, convince their reason, awaken their conscience.', 45228, 0), (471915, 'We''re so much more likely to feel sympathy for an animal than another person; thus, the best fiction uses animals to define truly humane behavior.', 30, 0), (471916, 'In 1800, in the first interparty contest, the Federalists warned that presidential candidate Thomas Jefferson, because of his sympathy expressed at the outset of the French Revolution, was ''the son of a half-breed Indian squaw'' who would put opponents under the guillotine.', 19692, 0), (471917, 'Pierre Curie came to see me and showed a simple and sincere sympathy with my student life. Soon he caught the habit of speaking to me of his dream of an existence consecrated entirely to scientific research, and he asked me to share that life.', 1036, 0), (471918, 'Manhattan''s probably one of the bluest parts in the country, and Indiana''s definitely one of the redder states. I have sympathy for both sides.', 13056, 0), (471919, 'I would rather be kept alive in the efficient if cold altruism of a large hospital than expire in a gush of warm sympathy in a small one.', 17538, 0), (471920, 'It is the right of our people to organize to oppose any law and any part of the Constitution with which they are not in sympathy.', 70249, 0), (471921, 'Great grief does not of itself put an end to itself.', 65434, 0), (471922, 'I am convinced that, despite what you think of Obama, I don''t think Obama has a person-to-person connection with people. I think people love him because of his race and feel sorry for him, object of sympathy. I think people feel he''s a victim, he portrays himself as a victim of America; he gets sympathy that way.', 17531, 0), (471923, 'What is it that distinguishes you and me from the lower animals - from the beasts? More, I say, than anything else, human sympathy - human sympathy.', 67335, 0), (471924, 'Two nations between whom there is no intercourse and no sympathy; who are as ignorant of each other''s habits, thoughts, and feelings, as if they were dwellers in different zones, or inhabitants of different planets. The rich and the poor.', 1827, 0), (471925, 'I didn''t go to university. Didn''t even finish A-levels. But I have sympathy for those who did.', 195, 0), (471926, 'I''m not looking for sympathy at all.', 12194, 0), (471927, 'Marriage must be a relation either of sympathy or of conquest.', 215, 0), (471928, 'The mission of ''8 Mile'' is essentially to garner sympathy for a white rapper involved in an old-school shootout - a rap contest. This may be the final frontier for pop, more unbelievable than the prospect of launching a member of ''N Sync into orbit.', 68243, 0), (471929, 'Sympathy is one of the principles most widely rooted in our nature: we rejoice to see ourselves reflected in another; and, perversely enough, we sometimes have a secret pleasure in seeing the sin which dwells in ourselves existing under a deformed and monstrous aspect in another.', 20151, 0), (471930, 'Bear and endure: This sorrow will one day prove to be for your good.', 782, 0), (471931, 'I can''t understand why someone wouldn''t have a degree of sympathy for people that had to flee their country, travel to try and find their home somewhere, and nobody wants them. How could you not be a little bit sympathetic?', 69667, 0), (471932, 'I like the Rolling Stones for karaoke. ''Sympathy For The Devil'' is a great one.', 43985, 0), (471933, 'The community stagnates without the impulse of the individual. The impulse dies away without the sympathy of the community.', 1782, 0), (471934, 'I''m constantly amazed by the ability a child has to show sympathy, to read emotions, to get to the heart of any situation. It''s unfiltered and completely inspiring.', 54756, 0), (471935, 'I felt bad when George Bush was booed. But only briefly. My sympathy for that man has a half-life of about four seconds.', 12902, 0), (471936, 'We do not learn by inference and deduction and the application of mathematics to philosophy, but by direct intercourse and sympathy.', 9695, 0), (471937, 'Abstract sympathy with the working class as an economic entity is easy, but the feeling can vanish on contact with actual members of the group, who often arrive with disturbing beliefs and powerful resentments - who might not sound or look like people urban progressives want to know.', 14528, 0), (471938, 'I''m not sympathetic. I have zero sympathy. I understand about emotional eating, I understand how painful the process can be, but I also understand that change is possible.', 1860, 0), (471939, 'My upbringing has given me sympathy for the idea of isolation and what it is to be a new person in the room, where everyone else has some amount of familiarity and comfort.', 433, 0), (471940, 'AI don''t make a big thing out of my race. If you try to preach, people give you a little sympathy and then they want to get out of the way. So you don''t preach; you tell the story.', 67019, 0), (471941, 'Increased sympathy for an Islamist cause, lack of integration, and the absence of acceptance of Muslims into British society makes it harder for Muslims to challenge Islamism and tough for non-Muslims to understand it.', 10487, 0), (471942, 'There''s a great tradition of actors taking on parts of much less obvious sympathy.', 68434, 0), (471943, 'Any sympathy won for Aileen Wuornos based on a lie is not sympathy at all. The question is, can we have sympathy for the circumstances of someone''s life? That''s what I was interested in.', 68686, 0), (471944, 'Fess up, ''Hunger Games'' fans: Does anyone care about Peeta or find him attractive? He''s the Ron Weasley of the series: he gets points for callow valor and sympathy for his run of bad luck, but he remains a pasty, earnest bore.', 67854, 0), (471945, 'I have no sympathy for debunking human achievements that, in the end, gave ordinary people liberty.', 68899, 0), (471946, 'It''s hard to penetrate characters who are very cut off and lack empathy and to do it with sympathy. It''s so easy to make a damaged character repugnant.', 2777, 0), (471947, 'I''ve never wanted sympathy votes in anything I do in my life.', 68264, 0), (471948, 'Despite my excellent mood, I don''t have any sympathy for Romney. If he''d been a good candidate he wouldn''t have had a different campaign for every month on the calendar.', 19519, 0), (471949, 'Sometimes, in the midst of a tragedy like the Newton massacre, we witness incredible acts of valor, tenderness, grace, and decency. We saw it from Sandy Hook Elementary School''s teachers, students, and parents, as well as from their community and country. The outpouring of sympathy and help has been touching and, at times, inspiring.', 68904, 0), (471950, 'I''m not going to give a courtesy gift to a person who''s going to win, and I''m not going to give a sympathy gift to a person who''s going to lose.', 71382, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (471951, 'The comic novels I did when I was in my 20s had a harder edge - less sympathy for people. Or a sympathy that was harder to detect: Characters'' foibles and obsessive bents were unrelenting, like caricatures.', 4572, 0), (471952, 'Most of my younger Native American friends are not in any way looking for sympathy, and they''re not looking to lay guilt on anybody. They have their dignity, and they do what they do.', 68267, 0), (471953, 'Personally, I have detested Gordon Brown since the moment in 2001 when he tried to make cheap capital out of the Laura Spence affair; as his troubles have piled up, I have felt no sympathy for him at all.', 30978, 0), (471954, 'I have every sympathy for writers. It''s a mystery to me what they do. I can edit. I can cross out and say, ''I''m not saying that'' or, ''How about we move this to here? Wouldn''t that make that bit of the story better?'' But where any of it comes from is beyond me. I will never write a play or a novel.', 11118, 0), (471955, 'As with the onset of sudden celebrity, for the newly rich, the world often becomes a darker, narrower, less generous place; a paradox that elicits scant sympathy, but is nonetheless true.', 67811, 0), (471956, 'With a film, you just don''t have time to build sympathy for the character. But I think we''re moving away from that in TV. With TV, you have a little more leeway to allow them to rise and fall and rise again and be much more complicated beings.', 60126, 0), (471957, 'One often calms one''s grief by recounting it.', 3285, 0), (471958, 'I take people very seriously. People are all I take seriously, in fact. Therefore, I have nothing but sympathy for how people behave - and nothing but laughter to console them with.', 850, 0), (471959, 'It''s not very interesting to establish sympathy for people who, on the surface, are instantly sympathetic. I guess I''m always attracted to people who, if their lives were headlines in a newspaper, you might not be very sympathetic about them.', 850, 0), (471960, 'The Who on record were dynamic. Roger Daltrey''s delivery allowed vulnerability without weakness; doubt and confusion, but no plea for sympathy.', 18483, 0), (471961, 'I damaged my health during ''Les Mis,'' which I didn''t want to mention in case it seemed like I was courting sympathy.', 67062, 0), (471962, 'In documentary filmmaking, there''s a tradition of telling stories about victims. We often do that from a very patronizing place, but mostly we do it from a very selfish place, to reassure ourselves that our lives are in sympathy and solidarity with the victims.', 68282, 0), (471963, 'I have sympathy for the people in Syria, and I do think there should be a worldwide response, but we should act cautiously.', 72131, 0), (471964, 'I''m a champion for personal differences. I have no sympathy for drug companies that can''t figure out how to make personalized medicine. We could generalize that to ''All society should be much more personalized.''', 68237, 0), (471965, 'I have a great deal of sympathy for reluctant readers because I was one. I would do anything to avoid reading. In my case, it wasn''t until I was 13 and discovered the ''Lord of the Rings'' that I learned to love reading.', 80, 0), (471966, 'Too often, we get attention and sympathy by being a victim. If we''re invested in someone being our villain, we must love being the victim. We have to let go of both characters in the story.', 37774, 0), (471967, 'The heart forgets its sorrow and ache.', 1247, 0), (471968, 'Those who peacefully gather to express sympathy for the family of Michael Brown must have their rights respected at all times. And journalists must not be harassed or prevented from covering a story that needs to be told.', 71441, 0), (471969, 'Sympathy is the first condition of criticism.', 4754, 0), (471970, 'All sympathy not consistent with acknowledged virtue is but disguised selfishness.', 1910, 0), (471971, 'Labor should be recognized as entitled to consult with management in the mutual interest. Labor cannot be driven, and business cannot be successful unless the men employed in it are enthusiastic and loyal. That loyalty cannot be obtained with a big stick; it must be based upon fair dealing and sympathy.', 63087, 0), (471972, 'I am a believer in the evolutionary process, and yet I have sympathy for the friends of mine who are creationists. I don''t find the positions incompatible.', 74130, 0), (471973, 'To avoid becoming chronically unemployed, people need more than platitudes offering sympathy. Career reinvention requires encouragement and guidance.', 61422, 0), (471974, 'I have nothing but sympathy for the people who are forced to work with me. I''m better now at picking out those that want to play that game with me, and those that don''t.', 32294, 0), (471975, 'A lot of actors find it impossible not to ask for the audience''s sympathy. They have a need to twinkle.', 11190, 0), (471976, 'I spent three and a half years writing the novel ''Chang & Eng,'' about the conjoined brothers for whom the term ''Siamese twins'' was contrived, and when I think of these afflicted people, my only emotion is one of profound sympathy.', 6948, 0), (471977, 'I very much dislike the intolerance and moralism of many Christians, and feel more sympathy with Honest Doubters than with them.', 66803, 0), (471978, 'Barton Fink is just too self-important as an artist to get much sympathy.', 74324, 0), (471979, 'If men and women are to understand each other, to enter into each other''s nature with mutual sympathy, and to become capable of genuine comradeship, the foundation must be laid in youth.', 62533, 0), (471980, 'It''s a game that just takes so much out of you. Every aspect of your life has to be very narrow, very focused. Everything else has to go away. And because of that, I think it''s obviously not healthy. The last thing I''m looking for is sympathy.', 70513, 0), (471981, 'There is a joy in sorrow which none but a mourner can know.', 62538, 0), (471982, 'I have sympathy for young people, for their growing pains, but I balk when these growing pains are pushed into the foreground, when you make these young people the only vehicles of life''s wisdom.', 23289, 0), (471983, 'I have to have a character worth caring about. I tend not to start writing books about people I don''t have a lot of sympathy for because I''m just going to be with them too long.', 8957, 0), (471984, 'Like many people, most Libertarians feel empathy and sympathy for less fortunate people. But they know you can''t have perfection in a world of limited resources.', 45221, 0), (471985, 'The natural effect of sorrow over the dead is to refine and elevate the mind.', 944, 0), (471986, 'NFL fans have less sympathy for fallen players than the Romans had for blind Christians.', 68974, 0), (471987, 'There are times when a sports figure doesn''t deserve sympathy.', 68974, 0), (471988, 'I never ask for mercy and seek no one''s sympathy.', 62785, 0), (471989, 'Our late Leader, Dr. Sun Yat-sen, with his universal sympathy for all oppressed and his profound understanding of Jesus'' revolutionary spirit of love and sacrifice, carried on his revolutionary work for forty years and brought about at last the liberation of the Chinese people.', 67633, 0), (471990, 'My impressions of the Russian Revolution can be divided into two periods. The first period was when I showed deep sympathy. My second period is one of disappointment. This change was the result of close observation on the spot.', 67633, 0), (471991, 'I learnt pity, sympathy, and what it was like to be at the other end of the stick. Such lessons can''t be learnt in lecture halls.', 70280, 0), (471992, 'When you''ve been raised in care, rap music isn''t just about guns and sexism. They''re talking about real things you can hang on to, problems of identity that you have sympathy with. It''s not just about the music, with rap: when I was in care, it meant a whole lot more than that.', 70721, 0), (471993, 'If the terrorists have the sympathy of people, it''s much harder to find them. So we need people on our side, and that leads us to be responsible leaders of the world, show some concern with the problems.', 2935, 0), (471994, 'I have to express sympathy from the bottom of my heart to those people who were taken as wartime comfort women. As a human being, I would like to express my sympathies, and also as prime minister of Japan I need to apologize to them.', 67426, 0), (471995, 'Life has never been easy. Nor is it meant to be. It is a matter of being joyous in the face of sorrow.', 74002, 0), (471996, 'If we wait until our lives are free from sorrow or difficulty, then we wait forever. And miss the entire point.', 74002, 0), (471997, 'I have sympathy for anyone who finds consolation anywhere we can. And many people do find it in religious tradition as it has been. I mean, I love much of that tradition. But somehow, that just didn''t speak to me in the way that it does to some.', 10783, 0), (471998, 'As far as I''m concerned, I own my dogs as I own my body. My legs are with me when I take a shower, and I feel no shame. If I were to lose one, I''d grieve, and people would send sympathy cards, but it would be my condition that evoked the sympathy, not the fate of the leg. That''s like losing a dog.', 21483, 0), (471999, 'I don''t want to be entertained. I don''t want visuals or musicals. I don''t want a vacation. I don''t want to quit. I don''t want sympathy. The cry of my heart is ''Just Give Me Jesus.''', 9414, 0), (472000, 'The more sympathy you give, the less you need.', 5930, 0);
